c06", "parents": ["8a49f013e0d0641b0eb187892bad82e17be26278"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Nguyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1512663 - Show bookmark tags in UrlbarView rows. r=dao\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17078", "files": ["browser/components/urlbar/UrlbarView.jsm", "browser/themes/shared/urlbar-autocomplete.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "22b28921759054aa25d1bc4b78e3a2761af40d81", "parents": ["a3de18f0e694c78002f76cfdf228b673953aac06"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489440 - Fix nsFormFillController in presence of Shadow DOM. r=smaug\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17121", "files": ["toolkit/components/satchel/nsFormFillController.cpp", "toolkit/components/satchel/test/mochitest.ini", "toolkit/components/satchel/test/test_datalist_shadow_dom.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0d9a334f6ae8011d712a69c751aabd81e31764c7", "parents": ["22b28921759054aa25d1bc4b78e3a2761af40d81"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1489440 - Disable autocomplete in the XUL autocomplete bindings. r=dao\n\nWith the patch above we do find the input element, and try to autocomplete it\nnormally, which confuses some tests.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17143", "files": ["toolkit/content/widgets/autocomplete.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "605d15524a488ee41d9566f1f48904798cb188a8", "parents": ["0d9a334f6ae8011d712a69c751aabd81e31764c7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520924 - Added missing comma. r=eslint-fix", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_advanced_update.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "744ba6ab5e0cde764faaf12f79072b3dd2681a99", "parents": ["605d15524a488ee41d9566f1f48904798cb188a8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521284 - Don't hardcode config.log path in old-configure. r=nalexander\n\nBecause old-configure is only refreshed when, essentially,\nold-configure.in changes, hardcoded (absolute) paths don't necessarily\nmatch the build environment of the current build.\n\nSo instead, use an environment variable that we pass from python\nconfigure when invoking old-configure.\n\nAlso do dummy changes to old-configure.in so that old-configure is\nrefreshed at least once to get the environment-based value.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17077", "files": ["build/moz.configure/old.configure", "js/src/old-configure.in", "old-configure.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39d0c50a2209e0f0c982b1d121765c9dc950e161", "parents": ["744ba6ab5e0cde764faaf12f79072b3dd2681a99"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miko Mynttinen \u003cmikokm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518069 - Do not use transform separators for nsDisplayWrapList containing just nsDisplayTransform r=mattwoodrow\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16841", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ad20edb20e58f913e922dff27005fe088903e5e9", "parents": ["39d0c50a2209e0f0c982b1d121765c9dc950e161"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Miko Mynttinen \u003cmikokm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514653 - Use the reference frame of the first flattened effect when recycling the layer r=mattwoodrow\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17079", "files": ["layout/painting/FrameLayerBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f722c4dbd4ccc19911de8ad05423363e0b5b2da7", "parents": ["ad20edb20e58f913e922dff27005fe088903e5e9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1505222 - Pass TransformStyle::Preserve3d to WebRender more often for perspective display items. r=mattwoodrow\n\nSee the comment.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16768\n", "files": ["layout/painting/nsDisplayList.cpp", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-transforms/preserve3d-nested-perspective-ref.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-transforms/preserve3d-nested-perspective.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2195f346d368042482357dc178255030ca610265", "parents": ["f722c4dbd4ccc19911de8ad05423363e0b5b2da7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520455 - Don't use the minimum scale size on fullscreen state to avoid the layout viewport gets larger than the visual viewport. r=botond\n\nThis is a workaround. To properly fix the issue we need to fix both of bug\n1516377 and bug 1508177.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17103", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/helper_fullscreen.html", "gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/mochitest.ini", "gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/test_fullscreen.html", "layout/generic/nsGfxScrollFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ada22b635f8d13adb7725c2fcac51d0e12e3ed59", "parents": ["2195f346d368042482357dc178255030ca610265"], "tags": []}, {"author": "James Teh \u003cjteh@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518054: Move a11y focus event firing from richlistitem.current to richlistbox.currentItem to fix the All Downloads view. r=paolo\n\nThe All Downloads view removes and re-adds its richlistbox for performance reasons.\nHowever, after bug 1492326, this causes the richlistitem's .current property to be assigned before its binding is applied.\nSince the .current property fires a11y focus events, this means this property is overridden and thus the events never get fired for that item.\nTo fix this, move a11y focus event firing into richlistbox.currentItem.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16932", "files": ["browser/base/content/urlbarBindings.xml", "toolkit/content/widgets/richlistbox.js", "toolkit/content/widgets/richlistbox.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c46ba0dfc91c8f734dc36f8c6faa5c9be0638a21", "parents": ["ada22b635f8d13adb7725c2fcac51d0e12e3ed59"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cameron McCormack \u003ccam@mcc.id.au\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521652 - Run rustfmt on servo/ports/geckolib/. r=emilio\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17177", "files": ["servo/ports/geckolib/error_reporter.rs", "servo/ports/geckolib/glue.rs", "servo/ports/geckolib/stylesheet_loader.rs", "servo/ports/geckolib/tests/specified_values.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "989238f82c8949cbdb9a664d93f9313c0b5ab8e2", "parents": ["c46ba0dfc91c8f734dc36f8c6faa5c9be0638a21"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Glenn Watson \u003cgithub@intuitionlibrary.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521420 - Skip some redundant work during picture caching updates. r=jrmuizel\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17085", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/src/picture.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/prim_store/mod.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c25d82a5b24c0b66321417121f6e1f80d8e62004", "parents": ["989238f82c8949cbdb9a664d93f9313c0b5ab8e2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521564 - Add GetDocument to nsContentSink, r=mccr8", "files": ["dom/base/nsContentSink.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "305c7ed630542b9610b80608311313ad6e96172f", "parents": ["018c76dba8faaab24fb30c31766638ba52b275c6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520760 - Fix AVX2 detection to ensure we have all required CPU parameters. r=jrmuizel\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16994", "files": ["media/libjpeg/1520760-avx2-detection.diff", "media/libjpeg/simd/i386/jsimdcpu.asm", "media/libjpeg/simd/x86_64/jsimdcpu.asm", "media/update-libjpeg.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1e76cea31571ed9274acd577b515e2c928cd207b", "parents": ["305c7ed630542b9610b80608311313ad6e96172f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521478 - Update libwebp to v1.0.2. r=jrmuizel\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17110\n", "files": ["media/libwebp/AUTHORS", "media/libwebp/MOZCHANGES", "media/libwebp/NEWS", "media/libwebp/README", "media/libwebp/README.mux", "media/libwebp/src/dec/vp8i_dec.h", "media/libwebp/src/demux/demux.c", "media/libwebp/src/enc/vp8i_enc.h", "media/libwebp/src/utils/utils.h", "media/libwebp/src/webp/decode.h", "toolkit/moz.configure"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fe7e9442e6cc503ad0fa385a1c380e3b3a23b147", "parents": ["1e76cea31571ed9274acd577b515e2c928cd207b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Maries \u003crmaries@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to mozilla-inbound. a=merge on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser-contentblocking.js", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "19db0edfbc10ad8f540a0a3482bd78c0baf7246d", "parents": ["fe7e9442e6cc503ad0fa385a1c380e3b3a23b147", "44369796f148630ff496be99f77a5eeea41c7d23"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520310 - Disable SANDBOX_EXPORTS for the mingw-clang build as well r=bobowen", "files": ["security/sandbox/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d8e4a86e306a43a3675402068da51ed038d19414", "parents": ["19db0edfbc10ad8f540a0a3482bd78c0baf7246d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521243 - Show a warning for invalid declarations and filter icon for overridden declarations in the new rules view. r=mtigley", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/rules/components/Declaration.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/reducers/rules.js", "devtools/client/inspector/rules/types.js", "devtools/client/themes/rules.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65e0b8a04d1af93fb35ce946565b665767bf07c3", "parents": ["d8e4a86e306a43a3675402068da51ed038d19414"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Sylvestre Ledru \u003csledru@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1519636 - Ride along: Add more commits to the git ignore list r=ehsan\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17151", "files": [".git-blame-ignore-revs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7d46c1872ba7920465cdf33b52672a374a66e360", "parents": ["65e0b8a04d1af93fb35ce946565b665767bf07c3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521407 - Avoid rendering the computed property list if it is not necessary. r=rcaliman\n\n- Avoid rendering the computed property list is not expanded.\n- Avoid rendering the shorthand overridden computed property list if there is\nno overridden properties in the computed property list.", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/rules/components/Declaration.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8ae27ed8d8618522cd921dd85c51b500ad9f11a9", "parents": ["7d46c1872ba7920465cdf33b52672a374a66e360"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gabriel Luong \u003cgabriel.luong@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521270 - Add classes to the rule when it is uneditable or unmatched. r=mtigley", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/rules/components/Rule.js", "devtools/client/themes/rules.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9cd21938464de36b922639cb91b5f92d3ff7a502", "parents": ["8ae27ed8d8618522cd921dd85c51b500ad9f11a9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Noemi Erli \u003cnerli@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset d8e4a86e306a (bug 1520310) for bustages in filesystem_dispatcher.cc", "files": ["security/sandbox/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ed02a9881c0d43d5ab3e3040e878ed771dd1f10c", "parents": ["9cd21938464de36b922639cb91b5f92d3ff7a502"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Huang \u003ctihuang@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1508355 - Add a test case for assuring all \"Save ... As\" options honor the first party domain. r=baku,richard@torproject.org\n\nThis patch adds a test case which tests following \"Save ... As\" options:\n\n* File menu:\n  - Save Page As\n* Context menu in content pages:\n  - Save Page As\n  - Save Image As\n  - Save Video As\n  - Save Link As\n  - Save Frame As\n* Page Info \"Media\" Panel:\n  - Save As\n\nIt triggers the save process and checks if the OA of the saving channel\nhas the correct first party domain.", "files": ["browser/components/originattributes/test/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/originattributes/test/browser/browser_firstPartyIsolation_saveAs.js", "browser/components/originattributes/test/browser/file_saveAs.sjs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f709682e4a01b425d7b863d1e17b9496903a8ff", "parents": ["ed02a9881c0d43d5ab3e3040e878ed771dd1f10c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520310 - Backout the patch from Bug 1498695 and cast to void*. r=bobowen\n\nIn Bug 1462100 we started casting to void* because mingw doesn't do\nautomatic conversions like MSVC does.  In Bug 1498695 I backed out that\nchange because I (mistakenly) thought it wasn't necessary for mingw-clang\nwhen in actuality, I simply wasn't hitting the code path due to\nSANDBOX_EXPORTS being defined.\n\nSince we want to _not_ define SANDBOX_EXPORTS I need to put the original\npatch back in place.", "files": ["security/sandbox/chromium-shim/patches/with_update/mingw_noexports_casts.patch", "security/sandbox/chromium-shim/patches/with_update/patch_order.txt", "security/sandbox/chromium/sandbox/win/src/interception.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "754481bfbe992e8754ce9af79b5a33f9412d186f", "parents": ["0f709682e4a01b425d7b863d1e17b9496903a8ff"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Robert Strong \u003crobert.bugzilla@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520693 - Add test for the About Dialog policyDisabled panel. r=Felipe", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/disable_app_update/browser_policy_disable_app_update.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d94203c1f6b52716801969622868a56361af7cb5", "parents": ["754481bfbe992e8754ce9af79b5a33f9412d186f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-inbound to mozilla-central. a=merge", "files": [".git-blame-ignore-revs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "956bd26eec5a9174753b63931d1a927a59cd4716", "parents": ["ada22b635f8d13adb7725c2fcac51d0e12e3ed59", "d94203c1f6b52716801969622868a56361af7cb5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland.", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "62fee61d444bc1ad93d24cc3f27f62831100086a", "parents": ["c25d82a5b24c0b66321417121f6e1f80d8e62004", "956bd26eec5a9174753b63931d1a927a59cd4716"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mike Hommey \u003cmh+mozilla@glandium.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521666 - Do not try to package layout debugger files when layout debugger is disabled. r=dmajor\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17202", "files": ["browser/installer/Makefile.in", "browser/installer/package-manifest.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "07b6d1a0382ca33c58321f568a9e51d9e0d20423", "parents": ["62fee61d444bc1ad93d24cc3f27f62831100086a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521137 - The pres context's base min font size is dead code. r=heycam\n\nNobody uses it from js, and we only thread the value around in layout. Let's\nkill all this code.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D16999", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "docshell/base/nsIContentViewer.idl", "dom/base/Document.cpp", "layout/base/nsDocumentViewer.cpp", "layout/base/nsPresContext.cpp", "layout/base/nsPresContext.h", "layout/printing/nsPrintJob.cpp", "layout/style/MediaFeatureChange.h", "layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39f5f9728b69780ff7def7c5211e9e7d65e9287f", "parents": ["07b6d1a0382ca33c58321f568a9e51d9e0d20423"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daisuke Akatsuka \u003cdakatsuka@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521349: Skip the shortcut keys test on win ccov. r=jdescottes\n\nBecause browser_aboutdebugging_devtoolstoolbox_shortcuts.js test open/close the\ndevtools several times, it takes a long time comparing with other tests.\nAlso, since the win ccov is super slow, this test was timeouted.\nThus, skip the test on win ccov at this moment.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17173", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "05c2a41b98c967b24bb2eb317ea52789e86cfacc", "parents": ["39f5f9728b69780ff7def7c5211e9e7d65e9287f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521603 - Add a helper method to check if the top level content document hasn't yet got first contentful paint and there is high prio event pending, r=jesup", "files": ["dom/base/nsContentUtils.cpp", "dom/base/nsContentUtils.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8ad35cea96d9c6c64c7f6c5e9e8f57a6b04f161a", "parents": ["d94203c1f6b52716801969622868a56361af7cb5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ehsan Akhgari \u003cehsan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521582 - Only simulate onContentBlockingEvent from onLocationChange for top-level non-samedocument notifications; r=johannh\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17145\n", "files": ["browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d02c0a90a085a4f75fab25dba9fa305bd97d7532", "parents": ["8ad35cea96d9c6c64c7f6c5e9e8f57a6b04f161a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjrmuizel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1494924. Redo the calculation of paintRect. r=mattwoodrow\n\nThis changes the calculation to match what we do for SVG blobs.\nNotably, it takes the residual into account when computing the area\nwe want to paint into. This makes a difference if the fallback\nis happening at a fractional offset.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17178", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4b841cc68f4d4ad817412290a95290915649773b", "parents": ["d02c0a90a085a4f75fab25dba9fa305bd97d7532"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjrmuizel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1494924. SetPaintRect to GetBuildingRect(). r=mattwoodrow\n\nInstead of setting the item PaintRect to paintBounds we intersect it with the\nBuildingRect. This properly reduces the size based on clips and gives a big\nperformance improvement for clipped nsDisplayFilter items because we call\nCreateSimiliar surface for the size of building rect instead of the bounds of\nthe item.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17179\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2bd66516b97abfc669d8a123da1af6a8174cde11", "parents": ["4b841cc68f4d4ad817412290a95290915649773b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjrmuizel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1494924. Set the visible area of the blob to GetBuildingRect. r=mattwoodrow\n\nThis lets us get some of the advantages of clipped blobs by drawing less of the\nfallback blob while still not needing to rerecord and redraw the blob\ncompletely during scrolling because of the changing clip rect. It drops\nthe number of tiles requested on a reduced test case reduced from the Googled\ndoc from 60 to a much more reasonable number.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17180", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderCommandBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0a5759a02d0727f4fefeb4920db8158e1103258d", "parents": ["2bd66516b97abfc669d8a123da1af6a8174cde11"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to mozilla-inbound.", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/urlbar/.eslintrc.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/Panel.jsm", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/authenticate.sjs", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_URLBarSetURI.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_action_keyword.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_action_keyword_override.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_action_searchengine.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_action_searchengine_alias.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_autocomplete_a11y_label.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_autocomplete_autoselect.js", "browser/base/content/test/urlbar/browser_autocomplete_curso