author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522181 - multiple external protocol URL blocker behind pref, r=smaug", "files": ["docshell/base/nsDocShell.cpp", "dom/html/test/test_external_protocol_iframe.html", "modules/libpref/init/StaticPrefList.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "24ad7d6e7775e9ada0d86dd9068c9c99a099041a", "parents": ["5d64e252185c4521d414bd197e4159a2971c1617"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Benjamin Bouvier \u003cbenj@benj.me\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1509441: Remove HasGcTypes boolean type and just use bool instead; r=lth\n\nThe custom bool enum types are usually created to explicate the role of\narguments at call sites. That being said, they make the code less readable if\nthey're used a lot, which is the case for HasGcTypes. Moreover, since literal\nbool values are only passed in a few places, we are better off using an inline\ncomment than having a type just for this purpose.\n\nThis also removes unused booleans which were used to tell whether we needed to\ngenerate supressGC code. This has been removed in the meanwhile and is no\nlonger useful.", "files": ["js/src/wasm/AsmJS.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmBaselineCompile.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmCode.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmCode.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmCompile.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmCompile.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmGenerator.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmModule.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmOpIter.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmStubs.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmStubs.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmTypes.h", "js/src/wasm/WasmValidate.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmValidate.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e9ffcdc09fdd83c28201e11a54c2f51e1a22e0ab", "parents": ["24ad7d6e7775e9ada0d86dd9068c9c99a099041a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Benjamin Bouvier \u003cbenj@benj.me\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1509441: Simplify CompileArgs field names and CompilerEnv::computeParameters; r=lth", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmCompile.cpp", "js/src/wasm/WasmCompi