p the TypeScript allocation code to stop relying on zero\ninitialization (malloc instead of calloc) and we now use the constructor.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17228", "files": ["js/src/jit/BaselineCompiler.cpp", "js/src/jit/BaselineJIT.cpp", "js/src/jit/BaselineJIT.h", "js/src/jit/IonBuilder.cpp", "js/src/vm/JSFunction.h", "js/src/vm/JSScript.h", "js/src/vm/TypeInference-inl.h", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.cpp", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.h", "js/src/vm/TypeSet.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f745bbf9f347e1946210d1559ea93693dca68b30", "parents": ["9bab87de8e3c8be666f0bc459519b4f26d8483a3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1507066 part 2 - Rename JSScript::nTypeSets to JSScript::numBytecodeTypeSets. r=tcampbell\n\nThis makes it a bit clearer that it's just the JOF_TYPESET TypeSets and does not\ninclude the arguments/this types.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17229", "files": ["js/src/jit/Ion.cpp", "js/src/jit/IonBuilder.cpp", "js/src/vm/JSScript.cpp", "js/src/vm/JSScript.h", "js/src/vm/TypeInference-inl.h", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec1aa436aeff3fe194c7077dcbb18950b0b3c5d0", "parents": ["f745bbf9f347e1946210d1559ea93693dca68b30"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1507066 part 3 - Move the bytecodeTypeMap hint to TypeScript. r=tcampbell\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17477", "files": ["js/src/vm/TypeInference-inl.h", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.cpp", "js/src/vm/TypeInference.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ddf227b9fa75462ad55cd4cac39e3d81fda7c491", "parents": ["ec1aa436aeff3fe194c7077dcbb18950b0b3c5d0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1507066