yanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522507 - Update Windows ARM64 builds to Visual Studio 2017 15.9.6. r=froydnj, a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17728", "files": ["browser/config/tooltool-manifests/win64/aarch64.manifest", "build/win64-aarch64/mozconfig.vs2017", "build/windows_toolchain.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c92744fdd50eeb3d2799cbd6f1e48aa0bc996fe8", "parents": ["125829ceb0216a67231c0416ee7fe3b517100ad3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1273876 - Check the computed style _color_. r=birtles, a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17911", "files": ["layout/style/test/test_transitions_events.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aea1f9d170ef4f6085c0d6065f5f3b5d63218136", "parents": ["c92744fdd50eeb3d2799cbd6f1e48aa0bc996fe8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1273876 - Use 'transitionstart' event to detect the target transition has been started instead of using setTimeout. r=birtles, a=test-only\n\nAnd stop the transitions inside the event callbacks.  Also in this commit,\n`did_stop` flag was split into two dedicated flags for `five' and `six` elements\nrespectively to avoid success accidentally. And flip the flag usage, e.g.\ntrue if the transition finished at the same time of the transitionstart event.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DttQ2nLVYWU\n\nDepends on D17911\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17912", "files": ["layout/style/test/test_transitions_events.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "767ca8e22c4d1b9169f43c4f282495fd53a23dde", "parents": ["aea1f9d170ef4f6085c0d6065f5f3b5d63218136"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1515310 - Eliminate antialiasing fuzz from reftests. r=emilio, a=test-only\n\nThe text in the \u003cth\u003e element was causing intermittent fuzz due to\nantialiasing. This patch removes the text to eliminate the problem.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18092", "files": ["layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-in-transformed-scrollframe-1.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-in-transformed-scrollframe-2.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-in-transformed-scrollframe-ref.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-transformed-in-scrollframe-1-ref.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-transformed-in-scrollframe-1.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-transformed-in-scrollframe-2-ref.html", "layout/reftests/async-scrolling/position-sticky-transformed-in-scrollframe-2.html", "layout/reftests/position-sticky/nested-sticky-1-ref.html", "layout/reftests/position-sticky/nested-sticky-1.html", "layout/reftests/position-sticky/nested-sticky-2-ref.html", "layout/reftests/position-sticky/nested-sticky-2.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "42b45239eb53c9632b6a6896286481e83cd63791", "parents": ["767ca8e22c4d1b9169f43c4f282495fd53a23dde"], "tags": []}], "date": 1548890963, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10585": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521584: [win64-aarch64] Add win64-aarch64 release mozconfigs; r=froydnj\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17452", "files": ["browser/config/mozconfigs/whitelist", "browser/config/mozconfigs/win64-aarch64/beta", "browser/config/mozconfigs/win64-aarch64/devedition", "browser/config/mozconfigs/win64-aarch64/release", "build/compare-mozconfig/compare-mozconfigs.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b2a72b5a7d2e6ba66c619f96c4ec6e5d7f5b49c6", "parents": ["42b45239eb53c9632b6a6896286481e83cd63791"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522380: [win64-aarch64] Don't beetmove win64-aarch64 installers on release branches; r=nthomas\n\nThese builds aren't ready for general availability, so we don't want to publish\nthem. But we want to start building them now.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17453", "files": ["taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/beetmover_repackage.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "717d18b6def1cbff0cd07459675ff84efde251c5", "parents": ["b2a72b5a7d2e6ba66c619f96c4ec6e5d7f5b49c6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522380: [win64-aarch64] Build win64-aarch64 on release branches; r=nthomas\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D14665", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/build/windows.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-bouncer-sub/kind.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/target_tasks.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/bouncer_submission.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c7319aa82972b04272719c172e83fdf6e61d9d5a", "parents": ["717d18b6def1cbff0cd07459675ff84efde251c5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522380: [win64-aarch64] Add in-tree support for win64-aarch64 partner repacks; r=nthomas a=tomprince\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17454", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/release-partner-repack-beetmover/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-partner-repack-repackage-signing/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-partner-repack-repackage/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/release-partner-repack/kind.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/partner_repack.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/partners.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "90eaf95b4002b4ec6ba4c3e0f6ed8c9700096146", "parents": ["c7319aa82972b04272719c172e83fdf6e61d9d5a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1548907387, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "mozilla@hocat.ca"}, "10586": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nes-CL -\u003e 67b1d965951e\nit -\u003e a5568ae719dc\npt-BR -\u003e e49e563f6f7e\nru -\u003e d0dbcf0a4e6d", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4b59de65923cffd3fdde3f2637c2ad3e0260d44", "parents": ["90eaf95b4002b4ec6ba4c3e0f6ed8c9700096146"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nes-CL -\u003e 67b1d965951e\nit -\u003e a5568ae719dc\npt-BR -\u003e ba6a55c5c04f\nru -\u003e d0dbcf0a4e6d", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d797934c804f7af4ebd54ca9a4f4f7d8f2e81907", "parents": ["f4b59de65923cffd3fdde3f2637c2ad3e0260d44"], "tags": []}], "date": 1548918033, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10587": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522494 - Enable Feature-Policy for relaxing-the-same-origin-restriction WPTs, r=farre a=test-only", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/html/browsers/origin/relaxing-the-same-origin-restriction/__dir__.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "63b51834cc1d92c8feb2885a613b55497e2f1b63", "parents": ["d797934c804f7af4ebd54ca9a4f4f7d8f2e81907"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521577 - Don't block a MediaStream where at least one track is pulled. r=achronop a=lizzard\n\nWith the per-track pulling settings we have today it is clearly the intention\nof the producer to start consuming a track that has pulling enabled, even if\nthere are other tracks where pulling is disabled.\n\nThis patch fixes that, so that when a stream has at least one pulled track it\nwill append null data to other tracks (commonly video) if they are lacking\ndata.\n\nThis means that we still block an entire stream if all tracks have pulling\ndisabled - to maintain the status quo for media element capture, which is\nthe only push-only producer of data.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17611", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a7206b7354fbdfba4c7f5b0d6f3909bee7f1ab36", "parents": ["63b51834cc1d92c8feb2885a613b55497e2f1b63"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dennis Schubert \u003cdschubert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522755 - Ship eBay Scroll Anchoring intervention to Fennec. r=rhelmer a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17600", "files": ["mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/injections.js", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/injections/js/bug1522755-ebay-scroll-anchoring.js", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/manifest.json", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "97295735ed424b3a791e98cae8a34e48ad14a727", "parents": ["a7206b7354fbdfba4c7f5b0d6f3909bee7f1ab36"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andr\u00e9 Bargull \u003candre.bargull@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523558: Fix test condition in VMFunction::returnsData(). r=nbp a=lizzard", "files": ["js/src/jit/VMFunctions.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1a27e2f35d33bd014903cfa1f0a0c09fd54f3793", "parents": ["97295735ed424b3a791e98cae8a34e48ad14a727"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523788 - Allow gfx.webrender.{all,enabled} on non-Nightly channels. r=jrmuizel a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17988", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "72fd8e42b6cbb3cb580b1bc2ee29b6d4af4b1052", "parents": ["1a27e2f35d33bd014903cfa1f0a0c09fd54f3793"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522780 - [Wayland] Use MOZ_ENABLE_WAYLAND to enable wayland backend, r=glandium a=lizzard\n\nRecently we use GDK_BACKEND to enable/disable Wayland backend. That's good for testing but bad for distro deployment.\n\nWhen GDK_BACKEND is set it's propagated to child processes which may not support wayland thus they fail to run. Also when GDK_BACKEND=wayland is set Firefox fails to start when Wayland backend is not available.\n\nTo allow easy deployment let's use a specific MOZ_ENABLE_WAYLAND env which means to use a default available GTK backend (x11 or wayland) and don't fail when Wayland is missing.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17607", "files": ["toolkit/xre/nsAppRunner.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "72201a8d9d95ed3d4a8d88b2cfe446e1ccc149e9", "parents": ["72fd8e42b6cbb3cb580b1bc2ee29b6d4af4b1052"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Randell Jesup \u003crjesup@jesup.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523333: add setTimeout/Interval profiler markers for all uses r=mstange a=lizzard", "files": ["dom/base/TimeoutManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9df1f456d924ec6a3dc096d2c5e0e6da193d5a45", "parents": ["72201a8d9d95ed3d4a8d88b2cfe446e1ccc149e9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Guan-tin Chien \u003ctimdream@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522779 - Correct datetime picker panel background color r=dao a=lizzard\n\nI removed the \"active\" attribute in bug 1512489 and didn't realize there is a selector in this sheet.\nThese CSS variables was added in bug 1317581 to reset background color of the picker.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17764", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/browser.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0419384222dc56ac89a19062ad62d20749f9d337", "parents": ["9df1f456d924ec6a3dc096d2c5e0e6da193d5a45"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1431582 - Add reduced test case for 3d transform bugs. r=kvark a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17864", "files": ["gfx/wr/wrench/reftests/split/gradient-ref.yaml", "gfx/wr/wrench/reftests/split/gradient.yaml", "gfx/wr/wrench/reftests/split/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f2ea35d460169b553a44f269b8357037ad51cbc", "parents": ["0419384222dc56ac89a19062ad62d20749f9d337"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dzmitry Malyshau \u003cdmalyshau@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1431582 - WR support non-locally-rasterized split planes r=gw a=lizzard\n\nNow that we no longer guarantee that a picture with perspective transform is rasterized in local space, we need to ensure that the shaders don't apply perspective correction to the texture coordinates twice.\nFor that to be the case, we pass an extra flag to the plane splitting shader, and un-do the perspective correction if it's not enabled.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17854", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender/res/brush_blend.glsl", "gfx/wr/webrender/res/brush_image.glsl", "gfx/wr/webrender/res/ps_split_composite.glsl", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/batch.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/picture.rs", "gfx/wr/webrender/src/prim_store/mod.rs", "gfx/wr/wrench/reftests/split/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dc3e444e4a2ced7aeee4164899ef93c78582381e", "parents": ["8f2ea35d460169b553a44f269b8357037ad51cbc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Paul Adenot \u003cpaul@paul.cx\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523611 - Require libvpx \u003e= 1.7.0. r=dminor a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18085", "files": ["toolkit/moz.configure"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "34bde0c12172e514a8062c3aa83af6ba6ed94115", "parents": ["dc3e444e4a2ced7aeee4164899ef93c78582381e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1548928998, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10588": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nnl -\u003e d5f13e9c2e42\nzh-CN -\u003e c9df738c94cb", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5d3f8d82bf37e8faf90da579dec2667dfd4af74d", "parents": ["34bde0c12172e514a8062c3aa83af6ba6ed94115"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nach -\u003e 9300160acc36\naf -\u003e a4ff20b9c975\nan -\u003e eeb3e82df381\nar -\u003e 5d67fef57807\nas -\u003e 96fe168f9a99\nast -\u003e cb13c794006e\naz -\u003e 15992c564a73\nbe -\u003e 0082c2df6f42\nbg -\u003e ffaad3c3ace8\nbn-BD -\u003e 67cd393255d5\nbn-IN -\u003e c64c1a2da0e8\nbr -\u003e 5b3c18687169\nbs -\u003e 1d9d2923a596\nca -\u003e e9fc7cf3b504\ncak -\u003e 1126f8e988ef\ncs -\u003e 9ed6ebcd2a64\ncy -\u003e 7dba1baaa067\nde -\u003e dbb750acb363\ndsb -\u003e e9baa25ad54b\nel -\u003e a5c667271d72\nen-CA -\u003e 3573f3a661a7\nen-GB -\u003e 1ef9ff1ae9ae\nen-ZA -\u003e 33ef4eb7fc7d\neo -\u003e e1744cce5e3c\nes-AR -\u003e 6b82d0456e70\nes-CL -\u003e c4a49198bf11\nes-ES -\u003e 0a4a1c5315d4\nes-MX -\u003e 5b72cfd387dc\net -\u003e c6abdce2c872\neu -\u003e 502260abac7e\nfa -\u003e 4e0b66d55