520808 - Allow importing of history from Chrome even if it was created in the future. r=mak a=lizzard\n\nRather than aborting adding data, we set the history items to have the current date/time. This seems mildly better than throwing away the history data.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17830", "files": ["browser/components/migration/ChromeMigrationUtils.jsm", "browser/components/migration/ChromeProfileMigrator.js", "browser/components/migration/MigrationUtils.jsm", "browser/components/migration/tests/unit/Library/Application Support/Google/Chrome/Default/HistoryMaster", "browser/components/migration/tests/unit/test_Chrome_history.js", "browser/components/migration/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8f157b0d3c52b1d8330bfe4db697ad18530cbbaa", "parents": ["6edb580f40bf764b11502c0636e5059ba8552791"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523362 - Validate cursor data in TabParent::RecvSetCursor. r=tnikkel a=lizzard\n\nI think the `stride \u003c width * bpp` is the right thing to check for, since I\ndon't know if there's any guarantee of it of the stride being equal, but let me\nknow if I'm wrong.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17851", "files": ["dom/ipc/TabParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "575fb73398a7f5ba784c492f1c3583fdd1b32e09", "parents": ["8f157b0d3c52b1d8330bfe4db697ad18530cbbaa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1498639 - Give WR the id of the scroll frame perspective scrolls relative to, and compute the right transform based on that. r=kats,kvark a=lizzard\n\nI think this is as clean as it can get.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17848", "files": ["gfx/layers/wr/StackingContextHelper.cpp", "gfx/webrender_bindings/WebRender