 Mitchell \u003cdustin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524358 - get commit message locally, rather than from task parameters r=tomprince a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18288", "files": [".taskcluster.yml", "taskcluster/mach_commands.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/cron/decision.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/decision.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/test/test_decision.py", "taskcluster/taskgraph/util/hg.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a142aefab93abd44861b92ddb3b4fe7756fcbd22", "parents": ["bbbacf423bdcdc5c4022ef23a31eb9cc681f8ebf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524243 - [marionette] Correctly handle script_timeout for WebDriver:{ExecuteScript,ExecuteAsyncScript}. r=jgraham a=test-only\n\nThis fixes the following regressions as introduced by\nbug 1510929 for the Marionette client.\n\n1) The custom timeout as set isn't reset if the\n   script times out.\n\n2) Fractions of a second for the script timeout are\n   lost because the division operates on decimal valus.\n   As such a timeout of 100ms will result in 0ms.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18214", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_execute_async_script.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9cf59044f067672a749b8bc8a68321893c96d97d", "parents": ["a142aefab93abd44861b92ddb3b4fe7756fcbd22"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524243 - [marionette] Correct calculation of timeout from milliseconds to seconds. r=jgraham a=test-only\n\nFractions of a second are lost because the division\nin getting the timeout value operates on decimal valus.\nAs such a timeout of 100ms will result in 0ms.\n\nDepends on D18214\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18219", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/timeout.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_timeouts.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6eeb1301ae9f2c0aaac9314bf78df9d515e6b342", "parents": ["9cf59044f067672a749b8bc8a68321893c96d97d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bas Schouten \u003cbschouten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521368 - Part 3: Ensure DrawTargetDual properly implements IsValid(). r=rhunt a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18383", "files": ["gfx/2d/DrawTargetDual.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e86470dd4c333f36a6f858e501f2fb7927c297f9", "parents": ["6eeb1301ae9f2c0aaac9314bf78df9d515e6b342"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549299439, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10617": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nathan Froyd \u003cfroydnj@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1496566 - avoid processing non-existent thread event queues; r=mccr8 a=lizzard\n\nJust because we're calling into the component manager for a service\ndoesn't mean that we're on a thread that has an associated event loop to\nspin.  If we are lacking such an event loop, we shouldn't try to\nNS_ProcessNextEvent, because that will wind up asserting that there's no\nevent queue.  Instead, just yield with the expectation that some other\nthread is making progress on constructing the service that we want.", "files": ["xpcom/components/nsComponentManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "74d8b59043e1793036bdedb14445e3e59b6f7a51", "parents": ["e86470dd4c333f36a6f858e501f2fb7927c297f9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Francesco Lodolo (:flod) \u003cflod@lodolo.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523243 - Update URLs in LEO searchplugin, remove Romansh variant r=mkaply a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17803", "files": ["browser/components/search/searchplugins/leo_ende_de-rm.xml", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/leo_ende_de.xml", "browser/components/search/searchplugins/list.json", "mobile/android/components/search/searchplugins/leo_ende_de.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5e9cc0eb20409ce001ed024890a4b6dbcbd4d02c", "parents": ["74d8b59043e1793036bdedb14445e3e59b6f7a51"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Gaynor \u003cagaynor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1513687 - remove chromium's random code from IPC in favor of our own; r=froydnj a=lizzard\n\nThis includes deleting several unused functions. Our own code does a better job\nof using the preferred platform APIs for random numbers.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18120", "files": ["ipc/chromium/moz.build", "ipc/chromium/src/base/rand_util.cc", "ipc/chromium/src/base/rand_util.h", "ipc/chromium/src/base/rand_util_posix.cc", "ipc/chromium/src/base/rand_util_win.cc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "764910a1fa7e4f4d334734397035770b192b0aff", "parents": ["5e9cc0eb20409ce001ed024890a4b6dbcbd4d02c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Haik Aftandilian \u003chaftandilian@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1506495 - Whitelist /Library and ~/Library ColorSync Profile directories r=Alex_Gaynor a=lizzard\n\nWhitelist the /Library and ~/Library ColorSync profile directories allowing gfx.color_management.display_profile to be used to load color profiles from those locations.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18390", "files": ["security/sandbox/mac/SandboxPolicies.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "63b220f22addd222434d43e0ba0d46e263b58916", "parents": ["764910a1fa7e4f4d334734397035770b192b0aff"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjrmuizel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1506495. Fallback to the system profile if we can't read the file for the profile. r=aosmond a=lizzard\n\nThis is a better default than just assuming no profile.", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "864ba4d0315680df488437a8c31a9c3de8040164", "parents": ["63b220f22addd222434d43e0ba0d46e263b58916"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523285 - Don't clip outlines of a button input and such. r=bzbarsky a=lizzard\n\nSorry, should've seen this :(\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17834", "files": ["layout/forms/nsHTMLButtonControlFrame.cpp", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-ui/outline-021.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/css/css-ui/reference/outline-021-notref.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9ab060b915fbe70bdf85fd48d783d80cc76b189c", "parents": ["864ba4d0315680df488437a8c31a9c3de8040164"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549302504, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10618": {"changesets": [{"author": "Bas Schouten \u003cbschouten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524554: Ensure Canvas surfaces are initialized on the main thread and ensure their validity. r=rhunt a=lizzard\n\nThis isn't the prettiest solution but it's minimally invasive. More long-term a better solution may be to expose a call on DrawTargets to ensure their initialization even if they're on the main thread. IsValid probably isn't a good candidate for this as we want it to be usable freely on the main thread to ensure none of the basic conditions of the surface are still valid.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18339", "files": ["gfx/2d/DrawTargetD2D1.cpp", "gfx/layers/PersistentBufferProvider.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "02146faf5ac13099a1e6a9d2ef1251f8b6bda0f3", "parents": ["9ab060b915fbe70bdf85fd48d783d80cc76b189c"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_66_0b5_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_66_0b5_RELEASE", "FENNEC_66_0b5_BUILD1", "FENNEC_66_0b5_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_66_0b5_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_66_0b5_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1549303997, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ccoroiu@mozilla.com"}, "10619": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 02146faf5ac13099a1e6a9d2ef1251f8b6bda0f3 with FENNEC_66_0b5_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bdc2e1fdc63d96fdb1e4e6c9fb4e8df0b3cc75db", "parents": ["02146faf5ac13099a1e6a9d2ef1251f8b6bda0f3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549316086, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10620": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 02146faf5ac13099a1e6a9d2ef1251f8b6bda0f3 with DEVEDITION_66_0b5_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3ef8d20e65e2b79365f2ae8efa295540dbba507d", "parents": ["bdc2e1fdc63d96fdb1e4e6c9fb4e8df0b3cc75db"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549316270, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10621": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 02146faf5ac13099a1e6a9d2ef1251f8b6bda0f3 with FIREFOX_66_0b5_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7c9580d97f76906fddd903068a55f1e159c5856e", "parents": ["3ef8d20e65e2b79365f2ae8efa295540dbba507d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549316450, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10622": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncak -\u003e 17b3108701a4\ncs -\u003e 58f7ffbf7b5c\nit -\u003e 965dffa1298e\nnb-NO -\u003e 67568c2c1c00\nsq -\u003e 41b2133fea79\ntr -\u003e c1f4c9a19991", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb64a69271d69e29e8e9f1c15b884ee369aa7915", "parents": ["7c9580d97f76906fddd903068a55f1e159c5856e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncak -\u003e 117d44e27848\ncs -\u003e 58f7ffbf7b5c\nfr -\u003e baf6e6a4541b\nit -\u003e 965dffa1298e\nnb-NO -\u003e 67568c2c1c00\npt-BR -\u003e 903c3df37ff1\nrm -\u003e 8d6aedcfe9ec\nsq -\u003e 41b2133fea79\nsr -\u003e 6bdec2929b0d\ntr -\u003e c1f4c9a19991", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "508eca5c21b6212dacca926d0513bbdd347da8eb", "parents": ["fb64a69271d69e29e8e9f1c15b884ee369aa7915"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549364429, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10623": {"changesets": [{"author": "Wes Kocher \u003cwkocher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525191 - Regenerate certs CLOSED TREE a=tomprince,timebomb-fix\n\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18632", "files": ["build/pgo/certs/cert9.db", "build/pgo/certs/key4.db", "build/pgo/certs/mochitest.client"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f4e6efbb6b2e859e2eb01c075dac5697bca02382", "parents": ["508eca5c21b6212dacca926d0513bbdd347da8eb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J.C. Jones \u003cjjones@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525191 - Regenerate all .pem.certspec files into their .pems r=try a=try,timebomb-fix CLOSED TREE\n\nSummary:\nScripts:\nhttps://gist.github.com/jcjones/b25e07de3a48c3ed084f0f9e26911693\n\n# From the above gist\n./jcj-regenerate-certspecs\n\n# This is a DER form, not a PEM.\nopenssl x509 -in security/manag