ase DONTBUILD", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc4c1b7b7864809ef15bfc8ad49fbc5e9a4bbae3", "parents": ["9cef500e71c6d5995295cae48ca513e17f3a8a3c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549643000, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10653": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging a9f6e3381fb3e64a6b872efa52a46afe4dd588e8 with FENNEC_66_0b6_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7a56e1dc2c2c0ad9fdb222000e099ff27c3d71f5", "parents": ["fc4c1b7b7864809ef15bfc8ad49fbc5e9a4bbae3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549643177, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10654": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging a9f6e3381fb3e64a6b872efa52a46afe4dd588e8 with DEVEDITION_66_0b6_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "efb5186d4870023396780adf45e5e44f2da92d8b", "parents": ["7a56e1dc2c2c0ad9fdb222000e099ff27c3d71f5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549643354, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10655": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Unset EARLY_BETA_OR_EARLIER. a=me", "files": ["build/defines.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e4896e3e5eb2e8caf0f17b4e49a1fdab07a91946", "parents": ["efb5186d4870023396780adf45e5e44f2da92d8b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549651759, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10656": {"changesets": [{"author": "Liang-Heng Chen \u003cxeonchen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504157 - Make onsize event triggered once. r=smaug, a=test-only\n\nAvoid the condition been checked twice.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18961", "files": ["browser/components/resistfingerprinting/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5a11b523f8e332b43d3d83277bb9d5947b919f1a", "parents": ["e4896e3e5eb2e8caf0f17b4e49a1fdab07a91946"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan-Ivar Bruaroey \u003cjib@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522773 - Reject any outstanding DOMMediaStream::TrackPort::BlockSourceTrackId() promise on teardown to avoid recent debug assert permafail. r=bwc, a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18590", "files": ["dom/media/MediaStreamGraph.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9b3d629cf829c77442955d7efd9101a73511f187", "parents": ["5a11b523f8e332b43d3d83277bb9d5947b919f1a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Rob Wu \u003crob@robwu.nl\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1498636 - Separate \"include\" variables from manifest defaults. r=ahal, a=test-only\n\nTest manifests may be included by multiple other manifests, optionally\nwith additional variables below the `[include:...]` section header.\nThese additional variables are specific to the manifest that contained\nthe \"include\" section, and should not inadvertently be shared with other\nmanifests that also happen to include this manifest.\n\nTo achieve that, store the defaults for included manifests in a (path to\nparent manifest, path to included manifest) tuple instead of just the\nincluded manifest.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18086", "files": ["testing/mozbase/manifestparser/manifestparser/manifestparser.py", "testing/mozbase/manifestparser/tests/test_manifestparser.py", "testing/mozbase/moztest/moztest/resolve.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc9047475850942b21cec35ed83c6f09666fa512", "parents": ["9b3d629cf829c77442955d7efd9101a73511f187"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549652701, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10657": {"changesets": [{"author": "Oriol Brufau \u003coriol-bugzilla@hotmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522820 - Disable browser action's \"Remove Extension\" if the addon can't be uninstalled. r=Felipe a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18493", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bc23b491541e589b832b4605f188c22260f0f957", "parents": ["fc9047475850942b21cec35ed83c6f09666fa512"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523696 - Wait until the style attribute is applied to the dialog before sizing it. r=Gijs a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19037", "files": ["browser/base/content/sanitizeDialog.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b61d0fdc785b3dd4deafd0e29a3a3116d52cc11f", "parents": ["bc23b491541e589b832b4605f188c22260f0f957"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524210 - Only clear the richlistbox selection when the box itself is clicked if the richlistbox is of multiselection type. r=Gijs a=lizzard\n\nThere are a couple ways to fix this specific bug in Preferences. We could expand the padding up to the start border and remove the margin, though there would still exist a 1px padding on the richlistbox. Historically this code, at least for Preferences, was impossible to hit. The scrollbox couldn't get clicked because its size was defined by an inner xul:box that was the size of the richlistitems and whatever margin they had. Clicking next to the richlistitems in the Preferences before this regression was a click on the anonymous box and thus didn't clear the selection. Another potential fix could be if we added a special attribute that doesn't allow deselecting if clicking into nothing, but that seems like a band-aid that we would end up using in many other places instead of just removing this behavior.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18371", "files": ["toolkit/content/widgets/richlistbox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ee2b9d8d4b0b0b30c45d61977a979e3c7d762692", "parents": ["b61d0fdc785b3dd4deafd0e29a3a3116d52cc11f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jean-Yves Avenard \u003cjyavenard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525230 - Reset ImageRect when resolution change. r=bryce a=RyanVM\n\nVideoInfo.mImageRect is typically only used for VP8/VP9 content, however the Windows decoder use a common code between H264 and VP8/VP9 decoding and use this data to determine the image size. So we end up with conflicting image size and image rect (which contains cropping data).\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18976", "files": ["dom/media/platforms/wrappers/MediaChangeMonitor.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "daa824c92e14eb1a65c6e387ead711bc7730b630", "parents": ["ee2b9d8d4b0b0b30c45d61977a979e3c7d762692"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549669236, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "cbrindusan@mozilla.com"}, "10658": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kai Engert \u003ckaie@kuix.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526473, Export NSS_CMSSignedData_GetDigestAlgs and NSS_CMSSignedData_HasDigests in security/nss.symbols, r=jcj, a=lizzard", "files": ["security/nss.symbols"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d3f91dc5dfb47a91357c8276074fe57090bc5466", "parents": ["daa824c92e14eb1a65c6e387ead711bc7730b630"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549679955, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kaie@kuix.de"}, "10659": {"changesets": [{"author": "Chris H-C \u003cchutten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514031 - Record the value of some telemetry testing prefs. r=janerik a=lizzard\n\nWe're seeing some weirdness in the data that might be explained by these\nprefs being set to some non-default value.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17153", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/app/TelemetryEnvironment.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "476f22e149ba9a9eef995cf3d90f42e44f82e5c4", "parents": ["d3f91dc5dfb47a91357c8276074fe57090bc5466"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514940 - part 1: Forcibly disable new keyCode/charCode value of keypress events if the document is Confluence r=smaug,Ehsan,kmag a=lizzard\n\nOld Confluence does not aware of conflated model keypress event (see UI Events\nspec, https://w3c.github.io/uievents/#determine-keypress-keyCode).\nAdditionally, Confluence can be hosted with any domains.  Therefore, we cannot\nuse blacklist to disable the conflated model keypress event only on it.\n\nThis patch checks whether current or parent document is Confluence with JS\nmodule, called KeyPressEventModelCheckerChild.  For kicking this module,\nnsHTMLDocument dispatches an custom event, CheckKeyPressEventModel, when it\nbecomes editable only first time.  Finally, if it's a Confluence instance, the\nmodule let PresShell know that we need to use split model keypress event in it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17907", "files": ["dom/events/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/events/test/test_bug1514940.html", "dom/html/nsHTMLDocument.cpp", "dom/html/nsHTMLDocument.h", "dom/webidl/HTMLDocument.webidl", "layout/base/PresShell.cpp", "layout/base/PresShell.h", "layout/base/nsIPresShell.h", "toolkit/actors/KeyPressEventModelCheckerChild.jsm", "toolkit/actors/moz.build", "toolkit/modules/ActorManagerParent.jsm", "xpcom/ds/StaticAtoms.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "59b0981f244c1d330541d4593fcafa2635c3ac6b", "parents": ["476f22e149ba9a9eef995cf3d90f42e44f82e5c4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523166 - Explicitly wait for the localized buttons before sizing the window to content. r=mconley a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17777", "files": ["toolkit/content/widgets/dialog.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "546e05b0e3d22b9957fff74c7c5a0f0c8617494f", "parents": ["59b0981f244c1d330541d4593fcafa2635c3ac6b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Back out bugs 1519918, 1524246 and 1523181 from beta. a=lizzard", "files": ["dom/base/Document.cpp", "dom/base/Document.h", "dom/canvas/CanvasRenderingContext2D.cpp", "layout/base/PresShell.cpp", "layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.cpp", "layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.h", "layout/base/nsPresContext.cpp", "layout/base/nsPresContext.h", "layout/style/FontFaceSet.cpp", "layout/style/GeckoBindings.cpp", "layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp", "layout/style/nsFontFaceLoader.cpp", "layout/style/nsFontFaceLoader.h", "uriloader/base/nsDocLoader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bfdf856d1c9a2d717f33bddf1dabad8776167805", "parents": ["546e05b0e3d22b9957fff74c7c5a0f0c8617494f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1549682365, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "10660": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nda -\u003e 651d2761a6dc\nes-AR -\u003e 81d3adcadfc7\nfi -\u003e d18a5ff955b5\nhe -\u003e a33b6206f90d\nit -\u003e 14d08abf2e7f\nnl -\u003e e0f421889392\npt-PT -\u003e 7cd86469be05\ntr -\u003e dc137bb5734f", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e235f01aae95976bfcf777893c3eba188431699d", "parents": ["bfdf856d1c9a2d717f33bddf1dabad8776167805"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e