lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20418\n", "files": ["gfx/gl/GLContextProviderEGL.cpp", "gfx/gl/GLLibraryEGL.cpp", "gfx/gl/GLLibraryEGL.h", "gfx/thebes/gfxPrefs.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa6574ad741f461a236e38872f1a405d702841d9", "parents": ["902eaa7d51f14d809e2c8a289ce57a42bb538899"], "tags": []}], "date": 1550878844, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jgilbert@mozilla.com"}, "10759": {"changesets": [{"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1504766 - Let explicit Dark and Light themes ignore the Windows 10 setting for accent color in title bars. r=ntim,Gijs a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19764", "files": ["browser/themes/windows/browser-aero.css", "browser/themes/windows/compacttheme.css", "toolkit/modules/LightweightThemeConsumer.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/LightweightThemeManager.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9fe883c6c1eb27d2e16aceba083b8081ec6f944", "parents": ["fa6574ad741f461a236e38872f1a405d702841d9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526609 - When interrupting the reflow of abspos kids, still account for the old overflow areas. r=bzbarsky a=lizzard\n\nOtherwise, if we're scrolled, the scroll frame will think that our scroll range\nwas reduced, which will in turn clamp the scroll position, which is not good.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19362", "files": ["layout/generic/nsBlockFrame.cpp", "layout/generic/test/mochitest.ini", "layout/generic/test/test_scrollframe_abspos_interrupt.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3c75057cd305fabb2a722960a429f9098a017954", "parents": ["b9fe883c6c1eb27d2e16aceba083b8081ec6f944"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1509847 - only move minimized windows behind unminimized ones, r=dao a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19181", "files": ["browser/modules/BrowserWindowTracker.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7afc2589d2cd268558ac274c2d6aa51caf209d3", "parents": ["3c75057cd305fabb2a722960a429f9098a017954"], "tags": []}], "date": 1550916739, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "cbrindusan@mozilla.com"}, "10760": {"changesets": [{"author": "sotaro \u003csotaro.ikeda.g@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1516834 - Check if CopyData succeeded. r=nical, a=lizzard\n\nWhen CopyData failed, an image does not have valid data. It should not be used.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19746", "files": ["dom/media/VideoFrameContainer.cpp", "dom/media/ipc/RemoteVideoDecoderChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9d3241ed6cc5a21adfa97431541565cf1f26c275", "parents": ["f7afc2589d2cd268558ac274c2d6aa51caf209d3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Back out bug 1522417 from Fx66. a=lizzard", "files": ["layout/style/nsFontFaceLoader.cpp", "layout/style/nsFontFaceLoader.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "59a0b8b45c1e6a010397244e9030d9e3c80e2d86", "parents": ["9d3241ed6cc5a21adfa97431541565cf1f26c275"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nicolas B. Pierron \u003cnicolas.b.pierron@nbp.name\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528829 - Restrict ExtractLinearSum to monotonous operation in infinite math space. r=jandem,sunfish, a=lizzard\n\nThanks to Bruno Keith & Niklas Baumstark from the phoenhex team for finding this\nissue and reporting it with a proper analysis.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20343", "files": ["js/src/jit/IonAnalysis.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "197546cf8331433a7428de57a377215867a4250d", "parents": ["59a0b8b45c1e6a010397244e9030d9e3c80e2d86"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Gaudet \u003cmgaudet@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1473830 - Mark OSR TypeBarriers for Null/Undefined/MagicOptimizedArguments as implicitly used, and don't eliminate them during DCE. r=nbp, a=lizzard\n\nType barriers are marked as Guard instructions, however, in OSR blocks guards\nare eligible for DCE. However, Null/Undefined/MagicOptimizedArguments have no uses\nassociated with them, and so get optimized out. To prevent that, this patch\nuses the ImplicitlyUsed flag to indicate to DCE that these barriers are not\neligible for elimination.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20388", "files": ["js/src/jit/IonAnalysis.cpp", "js/src/jit/IonBuilder.cpp", "js/src/jit/MIR.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d5cdb1c49f3983fb7f84d424f66e86622fce9d0c", "parents": ["197546cf8331433a7428de57a377215867a4250d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1550937366, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10761": {"changesets": [{"author": "Henrik Skupin \u003cmail@hskupin.info\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528836 - [marionette] Allow check_for_port to raise exceptions. r=automatedtester a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20311", "files": ["testing/marionette/client/marionette_driver/marionette.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a548506067f8decdabb5657f947fe28383b48515", "parents": ["d5cdb1c49f3983fb7f84d424f66e86622fce9d0c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nika Layzell \u003cnika@thelayzells.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1516240 - Hold a BrowsingContext reference when constructing in-process actors in BETA. r=farre a=lizzard\n\nSummary:\nThis patch is intended for the beta branch, to mitigate the crashing\ncase.\n\nReviewers: farre\n\nReviewed By: farre\n\nBug #: 1516240\n\nDifferential Revision: htt