", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1503745: Make widgets with empty bounds consistently hide themselves. r=karlt a=lizzard\n\nPreviously, popup widgets with empty bounds would not be hidden.\nNon-popup GTK widgets with empty bounds would be hidden during ResizeClient().\nSkipping the resize for popups is only appropriate when they are hidden.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17394", "files": ["view/nsView.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5f890c9359edaa25ed64bf38b089b4a98c0ab396", "parents": ["d1fb2e847334af3bf461d28d350ceda7074be92b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emanuel Hoogeveen \u003cemanuel.hoogeveen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522294 - Do the right thing if we happen to get an aligned region in TryToAlignChunk. r=sfink a=lizzard", "files": ["js/src/gc/Memory.cpp", "js/src/jsapi-tests/testGCAllocator.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2a50443802ba4760f9846ba8acc1835712c17bd6", "parents": ["5f890c9359edaa25ed64bf38b089b4a98c0ab396"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Luke Wagner \u003cluke@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529349 - Baldr: detect invalid section before code section during streaming compilation r=bbouvier a=lizzard", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/wasm/streaming.js", "js/src/wasm/WasmCompile.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e886d8a7a57bd08d1ca8b72d67c168c858fc035b", "parents": ["2a50443802ba4760f9846ba8acc1835712c17bd6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dana Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1527372 - write out and shut down DataStorage all at once so that clearing on shutdown works properly r=Ehsan a=lizzard\n\nIn bug 1470918, a shared thread was introduced that did the reading/writing work\nfor all DataStorage instances. To ensure all state was written out at shutdown,\nthe original patch implemented a two stage strategy that in the first stage\nqueued an event for each DataStorage that would write out its contents and then\nin the second stage ran these events to completion. This conflicted with how\nFirefox's sanitization implementation would make sure that data was cleared at\nshutdown, if requested by the user. If the DataStorage objects observed the\nfirst shutdown notification before the sanitization implementation, the existing\ndata would be queued for writing and any further updates would be prevented.\nThus, when the sanitizer tried to clear data held by DataStorage instances,\nnothing would happen and the data would be written to disk.\n\nThis patch fixes this issue by implementing DataStorage shutdown in a single\nstage that can run after sanitization. Since sDataStorages knows of the\nexistence of every DataStorage, we can simply iterate through its entries, queue\nwrite events for each one, and then run those events to completion in one pass.\n\nThis patch also fixes bug 1528019 (gDataStorageSharedThread could leak if\nNS_NewNamedThread failed) because the fix is trivial and not worth handling in\nan entirely separate bug.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20034", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/DataStorage.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/DataStorage.h", "security/manager/ssl/tests/gtest/DataStorageTest.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/head_psm.js", "security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/test_sss_sanitizeOnShutdown.js", "security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b07b355d59f79c00a89accc52f029d09bdda8ba", "parents": ["e886d8a7a57bd08d1ca8b72d67c168c858fc035b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521233 - Stop using --panel-disabled-color for identity popup state labels and the content blocking settings button. r=dao a=lizzard\n\nThis is to improve text contrast on OSX.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20909", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/controlcenter/panel.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4d2851ed4896e486b4b00ffaea383d988f81713c", "parents": ["3b07b355d59f79c00a89accc52f029d09bdda8ba"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529467 - Make TextInputHandler::HandleCommand() dispatch eKeyDown event r=m_kato a=lizzard\n\nCurrently, when IME sends a command with committing composition,\nTextInputHandler::HandleCommand() dispatches a *fake* `keypress` event\nfor making default event handler (e.g., focused editor) handle the\nevent.  However, we stopped dispatching `keypress` events for\nnon-printable keys.  Therefore, web apps cannot do that like us.\n\nOn macOS, simple conversion IMEs like Korean 2-set IME, behave\ndifferently if active application is changed.  E.g., on Safari,\nsome of them may never use composition string, but not so on\nChrome and Firefox.  So, this is what the case we need to emulate\nSafari's behavior.\n\nDispatching a fake `keydown` event for this purpose does **not**\nconform to UI Events because `keydown` events should notify web\napps of **physical** key state changes.  However, Chrome dispatches\nfake `keydown` events intentionally.  Therefore, we should follow\nthis hacky behavior for user experience.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20644", "files": ["widget/cocoa/TextInputHandler.mm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "af029ffaf0ff1fa524d3b0dac01e3e40ecd106b2", "parents": ["4d2851ed4896e486b4b00ffaea383d988f81713c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nico Grunbaum \u003cna-g@nostrum.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525341 - RTP audio jitter stat is not updating r=dminor a=lizzard\n\nRTP audio jitter stat is not updating because the playout frequency isn't being set\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20530", "files": ["media/webrtc/trunk/webrtc/voice_engine/channel.cc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cf5c156b86ceeda2be61619c3cb3aa26503876e5", "parents": ["af029ffaf0ff1fa524d3b0dac01e3e40ecd106b2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1481244 - Don't update the volume when stream is errored. r=jya a=lizzard", "files": ["dom/media/AudioStream.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "edb0544758a7243453f9f048cc558b98cfd0e53f", "parents": ["cf5c156b86ceeda2be61619c3cb3aa26503876e5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522923 - Turn off blocking autoplay on Beta. r=cpearce a=lizzard\n\nWe would enable blocking autoplay feature via roll-out (Normandy), not just fliping on the pref.\n\nTherefore, we would turn off the pref on Beta on Feb 25th, which gives us 4 weeks on and 3 weeks off on Beta. And then use Normandy to turn the feature on step by step.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20329", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d520fdd91a48f4e7b5f858f666363629f96bd0ca", "parents": ["edb0544758a7243453f9f048cc558b98cfd0e53f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511053 - Stop affecting the titlebar's height while dragging tabs. r=Gijs a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19268", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "370feb0729375ad9d0b65e3551fe0e0e2321995b", "parents": ["d520fdd91a48f4e7b5f858f666363629f96bd0ca"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551299002, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "rmaries@mozilla.com"}, "10790": {"changesets": [{"author": "Junior Hsu \u003cjuhsu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524264 - move noproxy textbox lower to hint as a global effect r=ewright,flod a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18981", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/connection.xul", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_extension_controlled.js", "browser/locales/en-US/browser/preferences/connection.ftl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0ccb6406ff135639a179f81d4502ffac7cddcda6", "parents": ["370feb0729375ad9d0b65e3551fe0e0e2321995b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nico Grunbaum \u003cna-g@nostrum.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1527526 - AudioConduit is reporting send instead of recv RTP stats r=dminor a=lizzard\n\nAudioConduit is reporting send instead of recv RTP stats\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19607", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/AudioConduit.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7bd928c859a554df57f30f2f7525c06fa6402fb1", "parents": ["0ccb6406ff135639a179f81d4502ffac7cddcda6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1527951 - Ignore WebP image's alpha channel when a frame is marked as opaque. r=tnikkel a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19994", "files": ["image/decoders/nsWebPDecoder.cpp", "image/test/gtest/Common.cpp", "image/test/gtest/Common.h", "image/test/gtest/TestDecoders.cpp", "image/test/gtest/moz.build", "image/test/gtest/transparent-no-alpha-header.webp", "image/test/gtest/transparent.webp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aecc839fd41caf60a010626eb209deccdbf859ef", "parents": ["7bd928c859a554df57f30f2f7525c06fa6402fb1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Olli Pettay \u003cOlli.Pettay@helsinki.fi\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1528034, make IsHostOrSlot null-safe, r=enn a=lizzard", "files": ["dom/base/nsFocusManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "20cd9dd27bfc31a54f8451837f941891374d3363", "parents": ["aecc839fd41caf60a010626eb209deccdbf859ef"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dragana Damjanovic \u003cdd.mozilla@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1516806 - Remove SPDY_VERSION2 telemetry probe. r=kershaw a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19138", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/ASpdySession.cpp", "toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/histogram-whitelists.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4171deeda04bb446358cc6d6c76bd6cf4f0cd45f", "parents": ["20cd9dd27bfc31a54f8451837f941891374d3363"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1470926 - Null-check mBoundFrame after calling SetSelectionRange on it. r=TYLin a=lizzard\n\nThis code was already handling the world going away, but did not handle the case\nof just getting unbound, which can happen if some selection listener (e.g.,\nAccessibleCaret) flushes layout.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20469", "files": ["dom/html/nsTextEditorState.cpp", "editor/libeditor/crashtests/1470926.html", "editor/libeditor/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "524a4774fe51436368c729ab6eebad22072c61a6", "parents": ["4171deeda04bb446358cc6d6c76bd6cf4f0cd45f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518581 - Require mocks helper in aboutdebugging head.js;r=daisuke a=lizzard\n\nDepends on D18234\nMost tests will now need to use the mocks helper to avoid loading the regular client-wrapper.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18235", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_addons_remote_runtime.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_connection_prompt_setting.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_debug-target-pane_usb_runtime.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_persist_connection.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_routes.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_runtime_connection-prompt.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_runtime_usbclient_closed.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_select_network_runtime.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_select_page_with_serviceworker.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_sidebar_usb_runtime.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_sidebar_usb_runtime_connect.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_sidebar_usb_runtime_refresh.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_sidebar_usb_runtime_select.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_sidebar_usb_unknown_runtime.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_system_addons.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_thisfirefox_runtime_info.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_thisfirefox_worker_inspection.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_workers_remote_runtime.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ba725018e9ab36cab501d12112c98b5af5b047f8", "parents": ["524a4774fe51436368c729ab6eebad22072c61a6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528140 - Wait for requests to settle after aboutdebugging tab is selected;r=daisuke a=lizzard", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_devtoolstoolbox_contextmenu_markupview.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_devtoolstoolbox_menubar.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_devtoolstoolbox_shortcuts.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9632ee1cefeebbfbc55a53f444e08d26df9a2909", "parents": ["ba725018e9ab36cab501d12112c98b5af5b047f8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dimi Lee \u003cdlee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1527658 - Use asyncClassifyLocalWithFeatures API in aboutPerformance. r=baku a=lizzard\nSummary:\nThe error happened because aboutPerformance provided an unused\nparameter to Classify API which is removed in Bug 1501458.\n\nCheck tracking protection tables via Classify API is not supported now.\nWe should use asyncClassifyLocalWithFeatures API instead.\n\nReviewers: baku\n\nReviewed By: baku\n\nBug #: 1527658\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19793", "files": ["toolkit/components/aboutperformance/content/aboutPerformance.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a81551b6fd6b9493252506570f220987935aa848", "parents": ["9632ee1cefeebbfbc55a53f444e08d26df9a2909"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551301039, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "rmaries@mozilla.com"}, "10791": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529312 - Allow DontCheckDefaultBrower policy to be false r=Felipe a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20525", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/Policies.jsm", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/browser_policy_default_browser_check.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "59045592dda92ee21d37e272d6a30f35ee74e65b", "parents": ["a81551b6fd6b9493252506570f220987935aa848"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Scott \u003cscott.downe@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529730 - Impression capping for spocs on hero\n\nReviewers: k88hudson\n\nReviewed By: k88hudson\n\nSubscribers: reviewbot\n\nBug #: 1529730\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20961", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/Hero/Hero.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2c312025ce11e2d86c9c431ad84332de8b4816df", "parents": ["59045592dda92ee21d37e272d6a30f35ee74e65b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528715 - Work around problems with forcing the autocomplete result's capitalisation. r=geckoview-reviewers,m_kato a=lizzard\n\nEven though using text.replace() is supposed to keep the existing spans intact,\nin practice the composition spans still get lost, even when the replacement text\nis identical (because there was in fact no capitalisation difference between\nuser-entered text and autocomplete result).\n\nOne approach to fix this would be to manually save the composition spans and\nsubsequently restore them afterwards, like we already do this a few lines\nfurther down below, in the other major code path through onAutocomplete().\nHowever while trying to generalise that approach, the most natural approach for\nthe caller to specify which spans it wanted to save was to pass a Predicate\nlambda to the state saving function, which for some reason led to strange\n\"Didn't find class\" errors.\n\nSo instead, we just restart input for affected IMEs (i.e. Sony's keyboard) to\nget them back into sync with the new contents of the EditText.\n\nTo avoid unnecessarily calling restartInput(), though, we only do this if the\nuser-entered text (which at this stage is known to correspond to the auto-\ncomplete result when compared case-*insensitively*) actually differs from the\nautocomplete result.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20487", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/toolbar/ToolbarEditText.java", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/InputMethods.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ab901cb2baa5ef1983a18a2c91d4a9b78ea8c313", "parents": ["2c312025ce11e2d86c9c431ad84332de8b4816df"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Maries \u003crmaries@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522039 - Changes default Touch Bar button set and replaces icon on Close Window button. r=bwinton a=lizzard\n\nReviewers: bwinton, mikedeboer\n\nReviewed By: bwinton, mikedeboer\n\nBug #: 1522039\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D17831", "files": ["browser/components/touchbar/MacTouchBar.js", "modules/libpref/init/all.js", "widget/cocoa/moz.build", "widget/cocoa/touchbar/private-browsing.pdf"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc92378333dc0669c98fc3d11a8ec2bb0b5119a1", "parents": ["ab901cb2baa5ef1983a18a2c91d4a9b78ea8c313"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan Hunt \u003crhunt@eqrion.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528436 - Add dxgi.dll to xperf_whitelist.json r=jmaher a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20742", "files": ["testing/talos/talos/xtalos/xperf_whitelist.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b281fad428520421d5d7a8aaff2cbbad814d461", "parents": ["fc92378333dc0669c98fc3d11a8ec2bb0b5119a1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551304288, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "rmaries@mozilla.com"}, "10792": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518581 - Move worker listening logic to client wrapper;r=ladybenko,daisuke a=lizzard\n\nThis will make it easier to mock the behavior\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18234", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/middleware/debug-target-listener.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/modules/client-wrapper.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/modules/moz.build", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/src/modules/workers-listener.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_select_page_with_serviceworker.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_workers_remote_runtime.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/mocks/helper-client-wrapper-mock.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7fc7867411b58196980f5f724f086b6250643750", "parents": ["3b281fad428520421d5d7a8aaff2cbbad814d461"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518581 - Remove unused parameters from openAboutDebugging;r=daisuke a=lizzard\n\nDepends on D18235\n\nThe two parameters in the openAboutDebugging are a leftover from the original helper of the old about:debugging.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18236", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/head.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cf46b5a6e3ed1f8db130127dca8d14b9fddb7cfa", "parents": ["7fc7867411b58196980f5f724f086b6250643750"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518581 - Silence worker updates if they are not required by the test;r=daisuke,ochameau a=lizzard\n\nDepends on D18236\nWorker updates are very hard to predict and we have many intermittents caused by pending requests\nfor workers while we destroy the client.\n\nDiscussed with @ochameau about the potential solutions, and disabling worker updates in tests that don't need them seems a good option. A complementary solution can be to wait for debugger-client waitForRequestsToSettle (different from our current helper in head.js).\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18237", "files": ["devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_devtools.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_select_page_with_serviceworker.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_serviceworker_multie10s.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_serviceworker_push.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_serviceworker_pushservice_url.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_serviceworker_runtime-page.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_serviceworker_start.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_serviceworker_timeout.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/browser_aboutdebugging_workers_remote_runtime.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/head.js", "devtools/client/aboutdebugging-new/test/browser/helper-mocks.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "571ad2687c2ea8b846d9468e493fae909eb35e78", "parents": ["cf46b5a6e3ed1f8db130127dca8d14b9fddb7cfa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Honza Bambas \u003chonzab.moz@firemni.cz\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518774, r=dragana a=lizzard", "files": ["dom/canvas/test/mochitest.ini", "xpcom/io/nsStringStream.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6bacdb768e5af3f69cc3977ff70219ffaebac0cf", "parents": ["571ad2687c2ea8b846d9468e493fae909eb35e78"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551305143, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10793": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jorg K \u003cjorgk@jorgk.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529202 - disable test test_sss_sanitizeOnShutdown.js for Thunderbird. r=keeler a=test-only", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "eccb1f5d6a0720aebc8f00172d72cf5254b3f2e5", "parents": ["6bacdb768e5af3f69cc3977ff70219ffaebac0cf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Gaudet \u003cmgaudet@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524419 - Incrementally touch stack on arm64 r=tcampbell a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19992", "files": ["js/src/jit/arm64/Trampoline-arm64.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "73317ecccd48354ebf0047a7a0d019783d7b70ee", "parents": ["eccb1f5d6a0720aebc8f00172d72cf5254b3f2e5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim D. Smith \u003ctdsmith@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529352 - Collect WebRender probes in release r=jrmuizel a=lizzard\n\nA handful of probes that are useful for measuring the performance of WebRender are not currently collected in the release channel.\n\nSince we're planning to begin deploying WebRender in release on an experimental basis in 66, we should make sure that these probes are available there, so that we can assess its performance.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20599", "files": ["toolkit/components/telemetry/Histograms.json", "toolkit/components/telemetry/histogram-whitelists.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b1350573ac7c6c294c8d5cae275e6cc45b9ffa43", "parents": ["73317ecccd48354ebf0047a7a0d019783d7b70ee"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Major \u003cdmajor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526276 - Add a fake unwind code to arm64 JIT function entries r=luke a=lizzard\n\nThis works around the issue where if the PC and SP don't change while unwinding our JIT frame, we'll fail the unwinder's sanity checks and it won't call our exception handler.\n\nIdeally we'd store proper unwind info, but that's a larger change for another day.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20858", "files": ["js/src/jit/ProcessExecutableMemory.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "17fb0284bb5d0ecc4e0f8e87d5738e19fcc6090d", "parents": ["b1350573ac7c6c294c8d5cae275e6cc45b9ffa43"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529248 - Clear-Site-Data header should consider executioncontexts flag only for 2xx response status, r=farre a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20502", "files": ["toolkit/components/clearsitedata/ClearSiteData.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e3d40984bde070c97bc3c3190cad373be57b78a9", "parents": ["17fb0284bb5d0ecc4e0f8e87d5738e19fcc6090d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530327 - Enable new certificate error pages on Release. r=nhnt11 a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21009", "files": ["browser/app/profile/firefox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cdfa53fd8d9c1555c4775e435350d0fa32f2040b", "parents": ["e3d40984bde070c97bc3c3190cad373be57b78a9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matt Woodrow \u003cmwoodrow@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1511358 - Don't include elements with z-index\u003c0 when looking for the max z-index in a display list. r=miko a=lizzard\n\nThis restores the previous behaviour (where a result \u003c 0 was ignored), since using a negative value means we place our overlay scrollbar/resizer behind non-positioned content.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20212", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGfxScrollFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ccc6779c8e4866a8f6fb7b65b96b59ef4e40104a", "parents": ["cdfa53fd8d9c1555c4775e435350d0fa32f2040b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jeff Muizelaar \u003cjrmuizel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1515823 - Disable Direct2D on Qualcomm devices. r=aosmond a=lizzard\n\nThere seem to be a number of problems with Direct2D on the Qualcomm\ndevices. This includes visual corruption from bug 1515823 and crashes\nin CHwRasterizer::RasterizeEdges from 1515387.", "files": ["widget/windows/GfxInfo.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb8a1b398f229ff4f7ce8b5d1234a08002ac8353", "parents": ["ccc6779c8e4866a8f6fb7b65b96b59ef4e40104a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551306964, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "apavel@mozilla.com"}, "10794": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tooru Fujisawa \u003carai_a@mac.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1527768 - Report dead object in unhandled rejections set properly. r=jandem a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19879", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/promise/unhandled-rejections-dead.js", "js/src/shell/js.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d2578f23e2f53775c1091ef4cfbe54c685bad32f", "parents": ["fb8a1b398f229ff4f7ce8b5d1234a08002ac8353"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551314052, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "rmaries@mozilla.com"}, "10795": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Prince \u003cmozilla@hocat.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526584: [win64-aarch64] Only add win64-aarch64 platform to balrog blog for firefox; r=mtabara a=release\n\nThis reverts the refactoring in 0734f7d57cd81464053e7ffacc8897fce1a27d61 so only the firefox blob\ngets the new platform. This was causing failure in the subsequent release promotion task, as it made\nassumptions about the structure of the balrog blob.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21494", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/release-balrog-submit-toplevel/kind.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "674dfdbb55e1db81c730b883bd89d409d567f844", "parents": ["d2578f23e2f53775c1091ef4cfbe54c685bad32f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551353367, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mtabara@mozilla.com"}, "10796": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nbn-BD -\u003e 543b43dffa36\nit -\u003e f69beb75ac98\nnl -\u003e 87cbb05c25c8\nro -\u003e 51ae132fb9c2\nzh-CN -\u003e 30c4602bcf8f", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6f58ab127796e1365885d258c0ea320c88e69ec4", "parents": ["674dfdbb55e1db81c730b883bd89d409d567f844"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\naz -\u003e 806903540157\nbn-BD -\u003e 543b43dffa36\ncak -\u003e 284640a84bda\ncs -\u003e 007af39f9bb5\ncy -\u003e 387831156f59\nda -\u003e 73dc50ad8f79\nde -\u003e 5de5e895a792\ndsb -\u003e 132131c78943\nel -\u003e 464d19093585\nen-CA -\u003e 093a75ee2f99\nen-GB -\u003e 38eccdf8658c\nes-AR -\u003e 33e307fbcae7\nes-CL -\u003e 6d4ac11e2313\nes-ES -\u003e 4507e7d6e1a9\nes-MX -\u003e d3469d792de6\neu -\u003e 0b9fa6bb3139\nfr -\u003e ce2e9e90097b\nfy-NL -\u003e 79b1162645ec\nhe -\u003e 5275afe76b1a\nhu -\u003e 2fad6723714f\nia -\u003e 18f7e6bcbff2\nid -\u003e 64c7ac32607f\nit -\u003e 6d05fcb09129\nja -\u003e d4e269bd9997\nja-JP-mac -\u003e 727d88e95ab3\nkab -\u003e 076d9281f2a8\nkm -\u003e 9f759debf53c\nlt -\u003e 64e946e1f8a5\nms -\u003e 3cad493eef06\nnl -\u003e 517c1e0bd509\nnn-NO -\u003e 7be25feb7944\npl -\u003e 530bd637478a\npt-BR -\u003e 95982df3ad89\npt-PT -\u003e 6736513fc8a4\nro -\u003e 4b7d95b5463f\nru -\u003e a12f1152ad56\nsk -\u003e d29a72d0569d\nsl -\u003e d43b4db13b4f\nsq -\u003e 1b6ccb57d2d1\nsr -\u003e ab16b9c46d99\nsv-SE -\u003e 4c219ef4ce6f\ntr -\u003e d07c0b17e5a4\nuk -\u003e 18607efe47ab\nur -\u003e efa5c96be09f\nvi -\u003e bd730704b809\nzh-CN -\u003e 3597efcd88dd\nzh-TW -\u003e 37f25873aae2", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6897eeee6ab58690ff5557c94bce16165cabb311", "parents": ["6f58ab127796e1365885d258c0ea320c88e69ec4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551366032, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10797": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524353 - Add a reftest to prevent regression. r=jrmuizel a=test-only\n\nThe Google weather search result widget has an SVG inside a transform,\ninside a scrollframe. The patch in bug 1523776 broke the clipping in\nthat the SVG elements would not get clipped by the scrollframe. This\nreftest exercises that scenario.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18273\n", "files": ["gfx/tests/reftest/1524353-ref.html", "gfx/tests/reftest/1524353.html", "gfx/tests/reftest/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "328a24b8e49e2313f134436e7dbe29df3680ccb3", "parents": ["6897eeee6ab58690ff5557c94bce16165cabb311"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551366800, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "10798": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nCLOSED TREE\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21518", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b1090ef7dc8bcaeb3ffdbc866ae074c744018a71", "parents": ["328a24b8e49e2313f134436e7dbe29df3680ccb3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551369400, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10799": {"changesets": [{"author": "Bas Schouten \u003cbschouten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526045 - Part 2: Verify all DrawTargets created through CreateOffscreenContentDrawTarget. r=rhunt a=lizzard\n\nPreferrably CreateOffscreenContentDrawTarget would create Capture DrawTargets when we intend to use OMTP. This is not the case at the moment though and changing this would likely introduce more unforseen issues. For now all of these calls basically mean a DrawTarget will be used on the main thread and we should use a no-op ClearRect to ensure that the DrawTarget is actually initialized. Since IsValid for the moment won't do this for DrawTargetD2D. (See bug 1521368)", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPlatform.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "46f0f4418eddc69b08f223b7766ef55725df3920", "parents": ["b1090ef7dc8bcaeb3ffdbc866ae074c744018a71"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Drew Willcoxon \u003cadw@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529642 - When using a search engine @ alias, the only results that should be shown are search suggestion results, including in private contexts r=mak a=lizzard\n\nWe already have a check for stopping the search when using an @ alais or restricting to suggestions. Move the check outside the block where we add suggestions so that it's used regardless of whether we added suggestions. Update the existing test to run in a private context.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21140", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/UnifiedComplete.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/unifiedcomplete/test_search_engine_alias.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3bb0dde9e64f4d299f17781180a805912e861a3f", "parents": ["46f0f4418eddc69b08f223b7766ef55725df3920"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Shane Caraveo \u003cscaraveo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530816 support RTA IDs in AddonRepository r=aswan a=lizzard\n\nAddonRepository validates IDs that are returned from AMO.  We\nneed to handle the case where we are using rta prefix for ReturnToAMO.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21389", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/internal/AddonRepository.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_AddonRepository.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "420d4410f71f9cc7a53c13885c973134e5b3bd9a", "parents": ["3bb0dde9e64f4d299f17781180a805912e861a3f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551372975, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "aiakab@mozilla.com"}, "10800": {"changesets": [{"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525357 - Don't allow third party installs if xpinstall disabled by policy. r=kmag a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18727", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/Policies.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/internal/XPIDatabase.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "67710331eb1f09878f5524b76490cf1730049f5e", "parents": ["420d4410f71f9cc7a53c13885c973134e5b3bd9a"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_66_0b12_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_66_0b12_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_66_0b12_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_66_0b12_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1551376920, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10801": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\naz -\u003e 8ad4c2ef5214\ncy -\u003e b575795a5ec5\nen-CA -\u003e 6be9c7193f2a\nen-GB -\u003e b92bf81e9042\ngn -\u003e 4fd27c20d94a\nit -\u003e dee2d93451cd\npl -\u003e 1de5a79f3512\npt-PT -\u003e 3f235682ecf6\nsv-SE -\u003e 35d21f4db664\nzh-TW -\u003e 0fc1d3884809", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bf393d217b1a8fe53f2bcf97f3f66c3074b0593c", "parents": ["67710331eb1f09878f5524b76490cf