r \u003cagaynor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1415508 - use Span in constructing a byte input stream; r=mayhemer a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20687", "files": ["dom/base/DOMParser.cpp", "dom/events/DataTransfer.cpp", "dom/fetch/BodyExtractor.cpp", "dom/file/MemoryBlobImpl.cpp", "dom/jsurl/nsJSProtocolHandler.cpp", "dom/xhr/XMLHttpRequestMainThread.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxSVGGlyphs.cpp", "image/imgTools.cpp", "modules/libjar/zipwriter/nsDeflateConverter.cpp", "modules/libjar/zipwriter/nsZipDataStream.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/ftp/FTPChannelChild.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/ftp/FTPChannelParent.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelParent.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpTransaction.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/wyciwyg/WyciwygChannelChild.cpp", "security/manager/ssl/nsNSSCallbacks.cpp", "startupcache/StartupCacheUtils.cpp", "toolkit/components/extensions/webrequest/StreamFilterParent.cpp", "toolkit/components/places/FaviconHelpers.cpp", "tools/fuzzing/interface/FuzzingInterfaceStream.h", "uriloader/exthandler/ExternalHelperAppParent.cpp", "widget/cocoa/nsClipboard.mm", "widget/gtk/nsClipboard.cpp", "xpcom/io/nsStringStream.cpp", "xpcom/io/nsStringStream.h", "xpcom/tests/gtest/TestSnappyStreams.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "70a034af6e4b3b25d341baabdf1e59d265e1bd38", "parents": ["9ab0c2f8e3fa69068aadb0634f6e262604d08f22"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525874 - [Linux/Gtk+] When mozilla.widget.use-argb-visuals is set disable toplevel window shape mask, r=lsalzman a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18947", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8986082a63e66dfe130fe689d2c8bca27a2920c5", "parents": ["70a034af6e4b3b25d341baabdf1e59d265e1bd38"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lars T Hansen \u003clhansen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521939 - Correct the offset for reading stack args on ARM64 (for mozilla-beta).  r=bbouvier a=lizzard", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmStubs.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dd3195cc539c4f909b12327443ea0ed6e5c0fcfe", "parents": ["8986082a63e66dfe130fe689d2c8bca27a2920c5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551474360, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10810": {"changesets": [{"author": "daoshengmu", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530588 - Remove duplicate copy of browserState in VRSystemManagerExternal::PushState. r=kip a=lizzard", "files": ["gfx/vr/gfxVRExternal.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a57747b9852b8f6990ce49a26680c723a708560b", "parents": ["dd3195cc539c4f909b12327443ea0ed6e5c0fcfe"], "tags": []}, {"author": "J.C. Jones \u003cjjones@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526023 - Web Authentication - add isExternalCTAP2SecurityKeySupported r=qdot,keeler a=lizzard\n\nWe support CTAP2 devices on one specific platform, making it hard for RPs to\ndecide whether or not Firefox will support the tokens they're asking for. This\nadds a non-standard method to divine that information while Firefox moves toward\nCTAP2 support.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19826", "files": ["dom/webauthn/PublicKeyCredential.cpp", "dom/webauthn/PublicKeyCredential.h", "dom/webauthn/tests/mochitest.ini", "dom/webauthn/tests/test_webauthn_isexternalctap2securitykeysupported.html", "dom/webidl/WebAuthentication.webidl"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ff2c3fd26b15d1e10df6e42aab71ee461e18196e", "parents": ["a57747b9852b8f6990ce49a26680c723a708560b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529713 - [Titlebar] Use Window manager decorations on GNOME again, r=lsalzman a=lizzard\n\nThis patch enables the shape mask in CSD and Window manager decorations mode\nwhen we're runnin on composited screen and mozilla.widget.use-argb-visuals is not set.\n\nAlso don't use shape mask with Wayland and GL backend. When shape mask is set,\nadvertise toplevel window transparency but don't advertise it\nas alpha to GtkCompositorWidget.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20726", "files": ["widget/gtk/nsLookAndFeel.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e91e23e30d4b131d66e55ed6f92a91cd011f3804", "parents": ["ff2c3fd26b15d1e10df6e42aab71ee461e18196e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew Osmond \u003caosmond@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520760 - Fix AVX2 detection to ensure we support the required CPUID version. r=jrmuizel a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20833", "files": ["media/libjpeg/1520760-avx2-detection.diff", "media/libjpeg/simd/i386/jsimdcpu.asm", "media/libjpeg/simd/x86_64/jsimdcpu.asm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d8af25e59ccfc1a05b2b220b3174cf19a88533a1", "parents": ["e91e23e30d4b131d66e55ed6f92a91cd011f3804"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528276 - Do not destroy the DebuggerServer in non-e10s when last frame connection is closed r=ochameau a=lizzard\n\nWhen reviewing https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1521052 I did not think about Firefox for Android which is not using e10s.\nThis means the main DebuggerServer will be killed when there are no connections left. Happy to discuss more about the preferred solution.\nThis is a regression in 66 and I hope to uplift a fix for this.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20830", "files": ["devtools/server/main.js", "devtools/server/startup/frame.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e089d94139746ea06377fb7f71df25e55e3edf69", "parents": ["d8af25e59ccfc1a05b2b220b3174cf19a88533a1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528276 - Add test for DebuggerServer.keepAlive;r=ochameau a=lizzard\n\nDepends on D20830\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20831", "files": ["devtools/server/tests/browser/browser_debugger_server.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8cd0839de6b06b2ed1c8fcf7bea7b2d1526574c", "parents": ["e089d94139746ea06377fb7f71df25e55e3edf69"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528276 - Set DebuggerServer.keepAlive for RemoteDebugger and GeckoViewRemoteDebugger;r=ochameau a=lizzard\n\nDepends on D20831\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20832", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/content/RemoteDebugger.js", "mobile/android/modules/geckoview/GeckoViewRemoteDebugger.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f50d84563bc574211361fca6fe90e67b0cdb8f14", "parents": ["a8cd0839de6b06b2ed1c8fcf7bea7b2d1526574c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1527151 - Reset securityUI.contentBlockingEvent on top level location changes. r=Ehsan a=lizzard\n\nWe had previously missed to call browser.updateSecurityUIForContentBlockingEvent on\nonLocationChange updates, to reset the contentBlockingEvent state. This would mean that\non tab switch the contentBlockingEvent state for benign pages would still be what it was\nset to on the last tracker page.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20328", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/test/trackingUI/browser.ini", "browser/base/content/test/trackingUI/browser_trackingUI_state_reset.js", "dom/interfaces/base/nsIBrowser.idl", "dom/ipc/TabParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bdc420ea17d6f2688cc1de7f433b5b2330b11983", "parents": ["f50d84563bc574211361fca6fe90e67b0cdb8f14"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551486581, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "dvarga@mozilla.com"}, "10811": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ted Campbell \u003ctcampbell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1527007 - Work around Windows fmod bugs r=jandem a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21407", "files": ["js/src/jslibmath.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d53e3a3bef07479fff7243d33d13f6ac38554ebb", "parents": ["bdc420ea17d6f2688cc1de7f433b5b2330b11983"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dale Harvey \u003cdale@arandomurl.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522053 - Copy global permissions into new browsers r=johannh\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21279", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/permissions/browser_autoplay_blocked.js", "browser/modules/SitePermissions.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "02370e541eb933f3798c3c6fe22be8cc89cf9476", "parents": ["d53e3a3bef07479fff7243d33d13f6ac38554ebb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dale Harvey \u003cdale@arandomurl.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522058 - Fix race in clearing global permissions. r=johannh a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21381", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/permissions/browser_autoplay_blocked.js", "browser/modules/SitePermissions.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7e003748ec6260407407f96076f892ad20ad07cf", "parents": ["02370e541eb933f3798c3c6fe22be8cc89cf9476"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Byron Campen [:bwc] \u003cdocfaraday@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526477 - Part 1: Fix typo causing us to go into the controlled role when interoping with an ice-lite endpoint. r=mjf a=lizzard\n\nDepends on D19232\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19233", "files": ["media/mtransport/third_party/nICEr/src/ice/ice_parser.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d380e82c33fb1a719acecd1df968aea3b63c7de1", "parents": ["7e003748ec6260407407f96076f892ad20ad07cf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan Hunt \u003crhunt@eqrion.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1520666 - Avoid flushing layout when accessing clientArea for the document scrolling element in certain cases. r=botond a=lizzard\n\nThis commit attempts to prevent a layout flush when accessing clientWidth\nor clientHeight on an element and the following conditions are met:\n  1. The document is not embedded in another document\n  2. The element is the scrolling element of the document\n  3. We are using overlay scrollbars\n\nThis matches a similar optimization in Chromium [1].\n\n[1] https://cs.chromium.org/chromium/src/third_party/blink/renderer/core/dom/element.cc?l=735&rcl=e95660c6c08b9b855ceebaf21a1614bc3df75ff8\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20020", "files": ["dom/base/Element.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb041ef6b3bfbb139f6603f8abef7bae6a4959b4", "parents": ["d380e82c33fb1a719acecd1df968aea3b63c7de1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Martin Stransky \u003cstransky@redhat.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530625 - Enable system titlebar on Gnome/X.org sessions due mutter Bug 1530625 and disable titlebar X shape mask on mutter/X.org, r=lsalzman a=lizzard\n\n- Detect current desktop session and disable shape mask on Mutter/X.org due to Bug 1530252 (mutter bug).\n- Use system titlebar on Mutter/X.org as we can't draw the titlebar reliably.\n- Remove widget.default-hidden-titlebar from prefs. When it's defined it overrides default titlebar detection heuristics now.\n- Don't use shape masks at all on Mutter/x.org. When system titlebar is hidden in this case (by user choice) it has opaque corners unless\n  argb visual is selected.\n- Use Window manager decorations on Gnome Classic session, that works better than client decorations.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21203", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.cpp", "widget/gtk/nsWindow.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a95052dd004316192c823033b4aad5e8dc6f2493", "parents": ["fb041ef6b3bfbb139f6603f8abef7bae6a4959b4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551489043, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "dvarga@mozilla.com"}, "10812": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529203 - Clear the module map when changing a Document's global r=bzbarsky a=abillings\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21718", "files": ["dom/html/nsHTMLDocument.cpp", "dom/script/ScriptLoader.cpp", "dom/script/ScriptLoader.h", "xpcom/ds/nsBaseHashtable.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f09554ca8cbab37de0187b6d67a25739a18ede4", "parents": ["a95052dd004316192c823033b4aad5e8dc6f2493"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1529203 - Add release build assertions around using modules with the wrong global r=jandem a=abillings", "files": ["js/src/jsapi.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4c7d56a0a897172ef44a9a63047ceba033ac49e1", "parents": ["0f09554ca8cbab37de0187b6d67a25739a18ede4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551517471, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "jcoppeard@mozilla.com"}, "10813": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Fennec l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\ncs -\u003e ca82bd4e78a3\ndsb -\u003e ac4a1ce647d6\nfi -\u003e 420cc1990452\ngu-IN -\u003e a9ad8dd75ba9\nhsb -\u003e 30b382bebbea\nhu -\u003e b6fa70