5ef6\nsl -\u003e e8eba5bfb7c8", "files": ["mobile/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a989d385af0d8112d7630efd92ba8ecd0812e0d0", "parents": ["99d77e9e30525eabcee95ea999c94a1671776fc0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nen-GB -\u003e 590a79481675\nes-AR -\u003e 69ddb6d2d2d9\nfi -\u003e caf58b9b979b\nit -\u003e 3bbd27ca0e7b\nlij -\u003e 391a5e12ba71\npt-PT -\u003e 186bf21877e6\nsk -\u003e c129eb74e7be\nsl -\u003e 3ad5679d94b4\nzh-CN -\u003e b985a897afe5", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "345693051a8a6e0a4043ced89b1017d6fb8b4f0d", "parents": ["a989d385af0d8112d7630efd92ba8ecd0812e0d0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551837628, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10833": {"changesets": [{"author": "Vlad Baicu \u003cvlad.baicu@softvision.ro\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1519418 - Replace MMA preferences with sharedPreferences. r=JanH a=lizzard\n\nSummary:\nPatch D16319 attempted to clean the MMA code and allow for easier debugging\nof LP deeplinks on dev builds. However it introduced a regression because the\nMMA preferences were being accessed by the initializing activity. By making\ngetDeviceId public and static, calling it from another activity would result\nin a null value returned. I have refactored the code to use shared preferences\nand remove the dependency on other activities.\n\nReviewers: JanH, petru\n\nReviewed By: petru\n\nBug #: 1519418\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21984", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/mma/MmaDelegate.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a68634dc411b49987bbbd6434602c9ffbc2c6ea", "parents": ["345693051a8a6e0a4043ced89b1017d6fb8b4f0d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brian Grinstead \u003cbgrinstead@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530288 - Center align the reload button in customize mode r=Gijs a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21323", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "de039c1269c376d1468a09f2d4ca334df7dbef38", "parents": ["9a68634dc411b49987bbbd6434602c9ffbc2c6ea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530367 - Toggle audio playback when clicking on blocked media in pinned tabs. r=dao a=lizzard\n\nThis attribute  was overlooked previously when moving away from _overPlayingIcon.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21436", "files": ["browser/base/content/tabbrowser.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "345a12b24b69a09d6eb0c8fe7df3f9ae4fa0cb9a", "parents": ["de039c1269c376d1468a09f2d4ca334df7dbef38"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Schuster \u003cevilpies@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530519 - Fix error handling in TransferableToIPCTransferable. r=smaug a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21836", "files": ["dom/base/nsContentUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ca92748672f1763548d554c1b5711d25318c33dc", "parents": ["345a12b24b69a09d6eb0c8fe7df3f9ae4fa0cb9a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1531867 - support light and dark subpixel AA masks in Skia on mac. r=mstange a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21763", "files": ["gfx/skia/skia/src/core/SkScalerContext.h", "gfx/skia/skia/src/ports/SkFontHost_mac.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9b08cd8e30587526c6d9cda23b6b4902ac0ae9d2", "parents": ["ca92748672f1763548d554c1b5711d25318c33dc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551838617, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "10834": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets r=release a=l10n-bump DONTBUILD\n\nes-AR -\u003e f3a98d67d68b\nit -\u003e 262fece54f4c\nmy -\u003e 7e121bf61b9a", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d65b3702be545d8323a54a46f8a236c83e0601dd", "parents": ["9b08cd8e30587526c6d9cda23b6b4902ac0ae9d2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551855625, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10835": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532171 - don't use light-on-dark mask when font smoothing is disabled on macOS r=rhunt a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22006", "files": ["gfx/skia/skia/src/ports/SkFontHost_mac.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cc04c5dab84a04c8ae648fbd95401b541553db2b", "parents": ["d65b3702be545d8323a54a46f8a236c83e0601dd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551856555, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "10836": {"changesets": [{"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 377496 - Improve auth dialog blocking heuristics. r=MattN a=lizzard\n\nThe fix in bug 1312243 introduced a maximum of three consecutive cancelations (controlled by a pref) that a user could perform until Firefox would prevent the page from showing more dialogs.\n\nThis, in my opinion, is a great idea. The implementation, however, has a major fallacy: It checks the inner window id in the well-meaning attempt to find user navigation or reloads and clears its internal counter when that window id changes. Unfortunately this also clears the counter on non-user-initiated navigations and reloads. I believe that the true intention of the patch was to cancel the auth dialog after 3 attempts, except if:\n\n- The user reloads the page on their own terms\n- The user navigates to a different site on their own\n\nWhich is what I plan to implement, using the same pattern we applied to implement temporarily blocked site permissions:\n\n- Temporarily store basic auth counter state on the browser object, as a map from baseDomain (eTLD+1) to number of cancellations\n- Reset this state only on user initiated reload\n- Reset the counter for a domain if the user has entered login data into the dialog and submitted\n\nThis would mitigate the DOS issue while hopefully not breaking any sites that rely on basic auth.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18019", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js", "browser/base/content/urlbarBindings.xml", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/nsLoginManagerPrompter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0999f29d8f02f68c5ae0cc0ad1d6f7bb75a17e59", "parents": ["cc04c5dab84a04c8ae648fbd95401b541553db2b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 377496 - Add a test for rate limiting the authentication prompt. r=MattN a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18229", "files": ["toolkit/components/passwordmgr/test/browser/browser.ini", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/test/browser/browser_basicAuth_rateLimit.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8e69471064c0645f43d84bcf06fb0bd2c3d1dbbc", "parents": ["0999f29d8f02f68c5ae0cc0ad1d6f7bb75a17e59"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johann Hofmann \u003cjhofmann@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1525267 - Move auth prompt rate limiting to nsIAuthPrompt2.promptAuth. r=MattN a=lizzard\n\nThis also changes the name of 'canceledAuthenticationPromptCounter' to account for the\nfact that we no longer count up when the prompt was cancelled, but when it was shown.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21680", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js", "browser/base/content/urlbarBindings.xml", "toolkit/components/passwordmgr/nsLoginManagerPrompter.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "666f0ce4c40f746e8623a540f73565b050865c94", "parents": ["8e69471064c0645f43d84bcf06fb0bd2c3d1dbbc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551880352, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10837": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matthew Noorenberghe \u003cmozilla@noorenberghe.ca\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1531443 - Clear the `lastProfileAutoCompleteResult` during a form history fallback search. r=jaws a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21587", "files": ["browser/extensions/formautofill/FormAutofillContent.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "533b15ae2bde4c8d89723855a73248d9a84e7d51", "parents": ["666f0ce4c40f746e8623a540f73565b050865c94"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551904445, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mozilla@noorenberghe.ca"}, "10838": {"changesets": [{"author": "Matt Howell \u003cmhowell@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1531689 - Prevent the stub from installing native AArch64 for version 66. r=agashlin a=lizzard\n\nReviewers: agashlin\n\nReviewed By: agashlin\n\nBug #: 1531689\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22189", "files": ["browser/installer/windows/nsis/stub.nsi"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "051a0830599b133e1d6b5eea37feefa2ad497c7a", "parents": ["533b15ae2bde4c8d89723855a73248d9a84e7d51"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Caliman \u003crcaliman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523305 - Show Font Editor in read-only mode for pseudo-elements. r=gl a=lizzard l10n=feature-removal\n\nAdds a new `disabled` property to the Font Editor Redux store applicable to all input fields.\nWhen inspecting a pseudo-element, this `disabled` property is set to true.\nThis allows the pseudo-element to be inspected, but prevents editing font property values because it's currently not possible to write them back to CSS rules other than element inline styles.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18364", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/fonts/actions/font-editor.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/actions/index.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontAxis.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontEditor.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontPropertyValue.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontSize.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontStyle.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/FontWeight.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/LineHeight.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/fonts.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/reducers/font-editor.js", "devtools/client/locales/en-US/font-inspector.properties", "devtools/client/themes/common.css", "devtools/client/themes/fonts.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6dd6bcd4c1427c0c7d0e8b7e66c7f5a55143cd34", "parents": ["051a0830599b133e1d6b5eea37feefa2ad497c7a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Razvan Caliman \u003crcaliman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526054 - Set target node in Font Editor according to selected node type. r=gl a=lizzard\n\nRefactors the logic so the target node on which the Font Editor operates can point to a parent node in case of text nodes without explicitly changing the node selection.\n\nThe target node is assigned to `this.node`. When that is null, it means the node selection is not supported by the Font Editor. This removes the need for the `isSelectedNodeValid()` method.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21387", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/fonts/fonts.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/test/browser_fontinspector_text-node.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "230fcfcad611c7bb7f186f2610cbe8d884b6c88d", "parents": ["6dd6bcd4c1427c0c7d0e8b7e66c7f5a55143cd34"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530657. Remove webrender user data properties from frames first, then destory them. r=jrmuizel a=lizzard\n\nIf we destroy at the same time as removal, then the destruction can destroy other objects which in turn might remove frame properties and mess up the frame property table.\n\nThis should cover all ways the webrender user data can get deleted from a frame property.\n\nThe nsIFrame::RemoveDisplayItemDataForDeletion bit doesn't seem necessary to fix the intermittent but I think it is still necessary.", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFrame.cpp", "layout/painting/FrameLayerBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e84952f939308cf1a262087b5d42c76600fd08c9", "parents": ["230fcfcad611c7bb7f186f2610cbe8d884b6c88d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "sotaro \u003csotaro.ikeda.g@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1386487 - Check if D3D11Device is obsoleted in D3D11YCbCrImage::GetAsSourceSurface() r=nical a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21830", "files": ["gfx/layers/D3D11YCbCrImage.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "494caa8f588da55abb9bf5eb1bfb045f77669693", "parents": ["e84952f939308cf1a262087b5d42c76600fd08c9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530220 - part1 : allow some non-printalble keys as supported user gesture inputs to activate document. r=masayuki,cpearce a=lizzard\n\n`carriage return` and `space` are common keys which user might use to start media, so we should take account them as supported user gesture inputs.\n\nAs their pseudo char code are zero, we have to check their key code in order to distinguish them from other controls keys such as shift, alt...\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21253", "files": ["dom/events/EventStateManager.cpp", "widget/TextEvents.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dc39216dfad387efd439083045062e323869a428", "parents": ["494caa8f588da55abb9bf5eb1bfb045f77669693"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530220 - part2 : modify test in order to test different kinds of keycode. r=cpearce a=lizzard\n\nExcept printable keys, we would treat `carriage return` and `space` as supported user gesture inputs for activating document. Other keys won't activate document.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21255", "files": ["toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser_autoplay_policy_user_gestures.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4b05bf628c6106f4d690a5da78e826f7ab3e80fc", "parents": ["dc39216dfad387efd439083045062e323869a428"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530220 - part3 : speed up test. r=padenot a=lizzard\n\nWe can listen for the `block` event to know whether AudioContext hasn't started yet which can speed up the test.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21256", "files": ["toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser_autoplay_policy_user_gestures.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "71e48c6607e6c53eed1de2256c5760fa6c1b18aa", "parents": ["4b05bf628c6106f4d690a5da78e826f7ab3e80fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530220 - part4 : separate tesing web audio with gum to another test. r=cpearce a=lizzard\n\nTesting web audio with GUM is not related with the original purpose of this test. In order to reduce the complexity of this test, separate this part as another new test.\n\nAlso modify the naming of functions, because Mozilla coding style is to use the camelCase for the name.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21257", "files": ["toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser.ini", "toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser_autoplay_policy_user_gestures.js", "toolkit/content/tests/browser/browser_autoplay_policy_web_audio_with_gum.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3b0bc8cad66fcf18a00a9185ff534aad7b45f7db", "parents": ["71e48c6607e6c53eed1de2256c5760fa6c1b18aa"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530557 - tabprompt dialog box size restrictions are completely broken, r=MattN a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22020", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/general/browser_double_close_tab.js", "toolkit/components/prompts/content/tabprompts.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1639f365cc4cf6034fca350ca332a5d2bf32c56b", "parents": ["3b0bc8cad66fcf18a00a9185ff534aad7b45f7db"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Beich \u003cjbeich@FreeBSD.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532851 - Unbreak BSDs build on powerpc64 after bug 1462566. r=bbouvier a=lizzard\nDefine R32_sig, R01_sig based on:\nhttps://github.com/openbsd/src/blob/master/sys/arch/powerpc/include/signal.h\nhttps://github.com/netbsd/src/blob/trunk/sys/arch/powerpc/include/mcontext.h\nhttps://github.com/freebsd/freebsd/blob/master/sys/powerpc/include/ucontext.h", "files": ["js/src/wasm/WasmSignalHandlers.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4e252aec24d866bc6ad408c05e8cea9d82b06be5", "parents": ["1639f365cc4cf6034fca350ca332a5d2bf32c56b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brendan Dahl \u003cbdahl@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530881 - Uplift CFF font fixes for MacOS. r=yury a=lizzard\n\nSummary:\nIncludes pdf.js pull requests:\nhttps://github.com/mozilla/pdf.js/pull/10591\nhttps://github.com/mozilla/pdf.js/pull/10604\n\nReviewers: yury\n\nReviewed By: yury\n\nBug #: 1530881\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22131", "files": ["browser/extensions/pdfjs/README.mozilla", "browser/extensions/pdfjs/content/build/pdf.js", "browser/extensions/pdfjs/content/build/pdf.worker.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "86214b1c530d73f230161888fad6a75c54575f6d", "parents": ["4e252aec24d866bc6ad408c05e8cea9d82b06be5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528961 - Ignore more leaks in WPT websockets on beta. r=jgraham a=test-only l10n=feature-removal\n\nReviewers: jgraham\n\nReviewed By: jgraham\n\nBug #: 1528961\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21977", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/websockets/__dir__.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8704ee5785b623ec8a9767e6dc6300a85fbbb171", "parents": ["86214b1c530d73f230161888fad6a75c54575f6d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551918174, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ccoroiu@mozilla.com"}, "10839": {"changesets": [{"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526355 - part1 : notify the front end side to show the blocking icon if the site is still being blocked after it's back from the bfcache. r=cpearce a=lizzard\n\nIn order to display blocking icon when the document comes back from the bfcache, we have to notify front end what's the current blocking status.\n\nAs the front end side would clear blocking autoplay information when nagivation occurs, and the media might not invoke the play again when they comes back from the bfcache.\n\nTherefore, we should notify front end side that the site is still being blocked, and we should show blocking icon for it.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21582", "files": ["dom/html/HTMLMediaElement.cpp", "dom/html/HTMLMediaElement.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cd093abd9a5cac10c51cdf4aea052ed5fef34d8d", "parents": ["8704ee5785b623ec8a9767e6dc6300a85fbbb171"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alastor Wu \u003calwu@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526355 - part2 : modify test to ensure we would get blocked event again when navigating from the bfcache. r=daleharvey a=test-only\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21583", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/permissions/browser_autoplay_blocked.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "30da98d1f31c6c15fdcd053a4107477df58185e9", "parents": ["cd093abd9a5cac10c51cdf4aea052ed5fef34d8d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Scott \u003cscott.downe@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1531604 - Fixing impression pos. r=k88hudson a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22167", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/CardGrid/CardGrid.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/DSCard/DSCard.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/Hero/Hero.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/List/List.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamImpressionStats/ImpressionStats.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/content-src/lib/selectLayoutRender.js", "browser/components/newtab/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js", "browser/components/newtab/lib/TelemetryFeed.jsm", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/ImpressionStats.test.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/content-src/lib/selectLayoutRender.test.js", "browser/components/newtab/test/unit/lib/TelemetryFeed.test.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "37e058d76eca1d1510bfdd4274e2b81742db4b0b", "parents": ["30da98d1f31c6c15fdcd053a4107477df58185e9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan de Mooij \u003cjdemooij@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1527148 part 1 - Fix an Ion polymorphic inlining issue. r=bhackett a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21540", "files": ["js/src/jit/IonBuilder.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5d767f7d3d488c96e6df5e927cc0349fc969adb9", "parents": ["37e058d76eca1d1510bfdd4274e2b81742db4b0b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brian Birtles \u003cbirtles@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1531277 - Check child container count in NotifyRefreshDriverCreated; r=dholbert a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21636", "files": ["dom/smil/SMILAnimationController.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b72048157f1839b41ea407be0606a8f3cee83e47", "parents": ["5d767f7d3d488c96e6df5e927cc0349fc969adb9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Matthew Gaudet \u003cmgaudet@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530958 - Disable unboxed objects by default r=jandem a=abillings\n\n(This patch is a rollup of the folloiwing two:)\n\nBug 1525579 - Add pref for unboxed objects r=jandem\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D18870\n\n***\n\nBug 1526451 - Disable unboxed objects by default r=jandem,tcampbell\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D19197", "files": ["js/src/jsapi.cpp", "js/src/jsapi.h", "js/xpconnect/src/XPCJSContext.cpp", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8d7186b2f9a6cc4ac5f13fb4c97106de0fdbead8", "parents": ["b72048157f1839b41ea407be0606a8f3cee83e47"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Dennis Schubert \u003cdschubert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532346 - Beta/Release - Land WebCompat Release test interventions in tree. r=miketaylr a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22168", "files": ["browser/extensions/webcompat/injections.js", "browser/extensions/webcompat/injections/css/bug1526977-sreedharscce.in-login-fix.css", "browser/extensions/webcompat/manifest.json", "browser/extensions/webcompat/moz.build", "browser/extensions/webcompat/ua_overrides.js", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/injections.js", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/injections/css/bug1526977-sreedharscce.in-login-fix.css", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/injections/js/bug1522755-ebay-scroll-anchoring.js", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/moz.build", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/ua_overrides.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "13bfcad39c39edcd4e3fc5b26fd62b25d338235f", "parents": ["8d7186b2f9a6cc4ac5f13fb4c97106de0fdbead8"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_66_0b14_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_66_0b14_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_66_0b14_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_66_0b14_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1551952352, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10840": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 13bfcad39c39edcd4e3fc5b26fd62b25d338235f with DEVEDITION_66_0b14_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ba6658b59ed348f6c90799a99c9b8ae37c47023b", "parents": ["13bfcad39c39edcd4e3fc5b26fd62b25d338235f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551977264, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10841": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 13bfcad39c39edcd4e3fc5b26fd62b25d338235f with FIREFOX_66_0b14_BUILD1 a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c372a6eec263db63748eeef48d169b239ec333e1", "parents": ["ba6658b59ed348f6c90799a99c9b8ae37c47023b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551977699, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10842": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003cffxbld@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No Bug, mozilla-beta repo-update HSTS HPKP blocklist remote-settings - a=repo-update r=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22486", "files": ["browser/app/blocklist.xml", "security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc", "services/settings/dumps/blocklists/addons.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a918c495018625ba496d2d92db07f006e8c679c9", "parents": ["c372a6eec263db63748eeef48d169b239ec333e1"], "tags": []}], "date": 1551987152, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "10843": {"changesets": [{"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528943 - Stop trying to retrieve raw keycode value when native virtual keycode is VK_PROCESS r=m_kato a=lizzard\n\nWe didn't dispatch keyboard events during composition.  Therefore, we tried to\nretrieve raw virtual keycode value when key messages come with `VK_PROCESS`\nunexpectedly.  However, the API, `ImmGetVirtualKey()`, is not usable for this\npurpose because it always returns `VK_PROCESS` if the key messages have already\nbeen handled by IME.  So, we can just stop using it since we need to expose\nsuch key messages as KeyboardEvent whose `key` value is `Process` and `keyCode`\nvalue is `DOM_VK_PROCESS`.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D20623", "files": ["widget/windows/KeyboardLayout.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aff13d214a3514d92f72f54c9f482b898927d6cc", "parents": ["a918c495018625ba496d2d92db07f006e8c679c9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bas Schouten \u003cbschouten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1526045 - Part 3: Ensure DrawTarget validity inside gfxBlur::InitDrawTarget. r=rhunt a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21900", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxBlur.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5892e926a68ca496e7b2539b2f0795239ca6d962", "parents": ["aff13d214a3514d92f72f54c9f482b898927d6cc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bas Schouten \u003cbschouten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1524554 - Part 2: Ensure DrawTarget validity for DTs created inside Canvas. r=rhunt a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21901", "files": ["dom/canvas/CanvasRenderingContext2D.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cc6fc6015015707bdacbeaf206679df6ff78b6d2", "parents": ["5892e926a68ca496e7b2539b2f0795239ca6d962"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bas Schouten \u003cbschouten@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1521774 - Part 2: Ensure a device is available when attempting to create a device context. r=rhunt a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21899", "files": ["gfx/2d/Factory.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "067b9599e2aa2f1ec5fdfb76b14753435fd65f93", "parents": ["cc6fc6015015707bdacbeaf206679df6ff78b6d2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552033522, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "10844": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dennis Schubert \u003cdschubert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533408 - Bump WebCompat GoFaster version number by 0.0.1. r=miketaylr a=lizzard\n\nReviewers: miketaylr\n\nReviewed By: miketaylr\n\nBug #: 1533408\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22511", "files": ["browser/extensions/webcompat/manifest.json", "mobile/android/extensions/webcompat/manifest.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5e58a2a1528ccc45528f74abd64433889db4909b", "parents": ["067b9599e2aa2f1ec5fdfb76b14753435fd65f93"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ed Lee \u003cedilee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533089 - HTTP Referer not set when clicking articles r=k88hudson a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22375", "files": ["browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/DSCard/DSCard.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/Hero/Hero.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/List/List.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/content-src/components/DiscoveryStreamComponents/SafeAnchor/SafeAnchor.jsx", "browser/components/newtab/data/content/activity-stream.bundle.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ac72aaf9c46efd190225262830e06f053080d357", "parents": ["5e58a2a1528ccc45528f74abd64433889db4909b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532685 - avoid opening help pages more than once by adding listeners to the actual dialogs instead of using utilityOverlay.js, r=jaws a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22300", "files": ["browser/base/content/utilityOverlay.js", "browser/components/preferences/browserLanguages.js", "browser/components/preferences/colors.js", "browser/components/preferences/connection.js", "browser/components/preferences/fonts.js", "browser/components/preferences/languages.js", "browser/components/preferences/sanitize.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "27212b825dee1e9b147ad2975853145a485e620c", "parents": ["ac72aaf9c46efd190225262830e06f053080d357"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552033854, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "nbeleuzu@mozilla.com"}, "10845": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nicolas B. Pierron \u003cnicolas.b.pierron@nbp.name\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532599 - Force expected crashes on unexpected magic values. r=jandem a=RyanVM\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22120", "files": ["js/public/Value.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5f4ba71d48892ddfc9e800aec521a46eaae175fd", "parents": ["27212b825dee1e9b147ad2975853145a485e620c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552036943, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "10846": {"changesets": [{"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1459222 - Firefox RC: push snaps onto the beta channel at ship_rc phase r=mtabara a=release\n\nFirefox RC: push snaps onto the beta channel at ship_rc phase\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21380", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/release-secondary-snap-push/kind.yml", "taskcluster/docs/kinds.rst"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "858a6e5a240a47d2f8a9dc8d29bc512417f773ab", "parents": ["5f4ba71d48892ddfc9e800aec521a46eaae175fd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552051297, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jlorenzo@mozilla.com"}, "10847": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1514992 - Update annotation for webrender. r=lsalzman a=test-only\n\nApparently we sometimes fall back to skia canvas with WebRender if ANGLE\nfails to initialize. This makes the azureSkia condition true, but the\ntest still passes because of WebRender's magical properties. This patch\nupdates the annotation to reflect reality, so we don't get unexpected\npasses.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21012\n", "files": ["layout/reftests/image-element/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1c0f11f4fd4bf7f36ed0d3a0d37c347f40ffe8b8", "parents": ["858a6e5a240a47d2f8a9dc8d29bc512417f773ab"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552060151, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "10848": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 13bfcad39c39edcd4e3fc5b26fd62b25d338235f with DEVEDITION_66_0b14_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "641653ef68b3b79744327675054a65fca442b874", "parents": ["1c0f11f4fd4bf7f36ed0d3a0d37c347f40ffe8b8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release DONTBUILD", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "10044cafb43ea212bcbd128867ef991405f4ca66", "parents": ["641653ef68b3b79744327675054a65fca442b874"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552062504, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10849": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mozilla Releng Treescript \u003crelease+treescript@mozilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 13bfcad39c39edcd4e3fc5b26fd62b25d338235f with FIREFOX_66_0b14_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE DONTBUILD", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f68eb43ec08db3641c8edabaaf939f9e93893ea5", "parents": ["10044cafb43ea212bcbd128867ef991405f4ca66"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552062690, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "10850": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mihai Tabara \u003cmtabara@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523699 - add WNP list for 66.0 r=flod a=release", "files": ["browser/config/whats_new_page.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f369baa1797a0849d622ee3724c293f476983ec", "parents": ["f68eb43ec08db3641c8edabaaf939f9e93893ea5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552063061, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "mtabara@mozilla.com"}, "10851": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1523598 - Don't let WR ride the trains to release on 66. r=jrmuizel a=lizzard\n", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxPrefs.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "233a047f681dcb48ff12eb54fe79e4b5e10abdeb", "parents": ["0f369baa1797a0849d622ee3724c293f476983ec"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552076196, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "10852": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532708. r=botond a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22756\n", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/LayerTransactionParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "51d306795184276ba5b837b644a8802b5aa29eb2", "parents": ["233a047f681dcb48ff12eb54fe79e4b5e10abdeb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552079682, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "10853": {"changesets": [{"author": "Logan Smyth \u003cloganfsmyth@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530549 - Ensure that _clearSteppingHooks() runs _after_ we pause. r=jlast a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21384", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/thread.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_stepping-10.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "13616d2ad00049ffa76ebdfc8b9702317a269d0c", "parents": ["51d306795184276ba5b837b644a8802b5aa29eb2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533389 - stop leaving an item in the application handler list when sorting/filtering, r=jaws a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22545", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8ec48086dfd3329592d38492ee6c8f76e090922b", "parents": ["13616d2ad00049ffa76ebdfc8b9702317a269d0c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Edouard Oger \u003ceoger@fastmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532098 - Update login instead delete then add. r=nalexander a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22346", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/content/aboutLogins.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "408920c5296e7f8e39ff3507d7fd903a5c0fade0", "parents": ["8ec48086dfd3329592d38492ee6c8f76e090922b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552080051, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "btara@mozilla.com"}, "10854": {"changesets": [{"author": "Csoregi Natalia \u003cncsoregi@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 408920c5296e (bug 1532098) as per request. a=backout", "files": ["mobile/android/chrome/content/aboutLogins.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d5a11a79f7bdfa73a6033e5198ae48c07791a4f7", "parents": ["408920c5296e7f8e39ff3507d7fd903a5c0fade0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552084250, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "10855": {"changesets": [{"author": "Yaron Tausky \u003cytausky@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1484524: Allow creating a StrongWorkerRef for IPC in the Canceling state r=asuth a=lizzard\n\nBy allowing the creation of StrongWorkerRefs in the Canceling state we\nensure that IPC will not fail and lead to crashes.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21920", "files": ["dom/workers/WorkerRef.cpp", "dom/workers/WorkerRef.h", "ipc/glue/IPCStreamSource.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f83ccafddfa29dc1b510d0d0d0803aac105b03b3", "parents": ["d5a11a79f7bdfa73a6033e5198ae48c07791a4f7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552085237, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "bugmail@asutherland.org"}, "10856": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 0 - Minor extension protocol handler cleanup. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nThese are trivial issues that I'd rather keep out of the main patch.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21444", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0379572257905b9f89f87c8efdb5e0b96dad6d2c", "parents": ["f83ccafddfa29dc1b510d0d0d0803aac105b03b3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 1 - Add ready promise to WebExtensionPolicy. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nThis adds a promise member to the stub WebExtensionPolicy objects that we\ncreate early during extension initialization which resolves when the real\nextension instance is ready to load content. This promise will be used by the\nextension protocol handler to delay loads until the framework is ready to\nhandle them.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21445", "files": ["dom/chrome-webidl/WebExtensionPolicy.webidl", "toolkit/components/extensions/Extension.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/WebExtensionPolicy.cpp", "toolkit/components/extensions/WebExtensionPolicy.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b7e78201e26c6bcfc297f63b89454cde29a09bce", "parents": ["0379572257905b9f89f87c8efdb5e0b96dad6d2c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 2 - Delay extension protocol requests until extension is ready. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nWe don't want extension protocol load requests to begin loading until the\nextension is far enough initialized to run code. If we load it before then,\nthe extension framework will either fail to recognize the extension entirely,\nor may begin running its scripts in an incomplete environment.\n\nThis patch adds a slow path which adds a promise handler and creats a stub\nchannel only in the case when the extension is not ready. In the normal,\nalready-initialized case, we take the more direct path.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21447", "files": ["dom/promise/Promise.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4d96aa8bbf572eba63bc7d0d6ccfee494869702b", "parents": ["b7e78201e26c6bcfc297f63b89454cde29a09bce"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 3 - Initialize stub extension policies in child during startup. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nWe already create early stub policy objects in the parent process during\nextension startup, so that early load attempts and policy queries can succeed\nduring startup and extension installation. This patch does the same for child\nprocesses, which likewise may be asked to load extension URLs early during\nstartup when they override the homepage or have pages loaded from session\nrestore.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21448", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/Extension.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionProcessScript.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d94de0e08f52bbfb54a140462b0a4d2fb5e84477", "parents": ["4d96aa8bbf572eba63bc7d0d6ccfee494869702b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 4 - Add tests. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21449", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_startup_request_handler.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-common.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "11506a4e0fd8088f20b70a27e96e9b3170c9d5fb", "parents": ["d94de0e08f52bbfb54a140462b0a4d2fb5e84477"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552094135, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "maglione.k@gmail.com"}, "10857": {"changesets": [{"author": "Dan Minor \u003cdminor@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532756 - Rename geckomediaplugin to gmplugin on Android; r=droeh a=lizzard\n\nIn Bug 1514043 we renamed the geckomediaplugin to gmplugin, but missed renaming\nit on Android. This prevents the plugin from loading, which breaks OpenH264 in\nWebRTC.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22502", "files": ["mobile/android/base/AndroidManifest.xml.in", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml", "mobile/android/geckoview/src/main/java/org/mozilla/gecko/process/GeckoServiceChildProcess.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "77dcf9bd89d01d422319bd2c8aeae598a38c4cb5", "parents": ["11506a4e0fd8088f20b70a27e96e9b3170c9d5fb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Akshay Kumar \u003cakshay.sonu@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528097 : Fix FIDO U2F support on Windows 10 19H1/20H1 Insider builds r=keeler,jcj a=lizzard\n\nU2F support, behind the `security.webauth.u2f` pref and exposed by `dom/u2f/U2F.cpp`,  was broken when using Windows Hello, as the correct options for compatibility weren't set. This patch sets up Windows Hello to handle U2F-protocol backward compatibility properly.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21844", "files": ["dom/webauthn/WinWebAuthnManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e8fd50fb1d542b3d357d9c67616ce59f63c8f9f9", "parents": ["77dcf9bd89d01d422319bd2c8aeae598a38c4cb5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530132 - Consider the cookie permission for the current request, ignoring the top-level one, r=Ehsan a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22456", "files": ["toolkit/components/antitracking/AntiTrackingCommon.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9374f09f9b175e8cb258106e46d8392e3793949e", "parents": ["e8fd50fb1d542b3d357d9c67616ce59f63c8f9f9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1533388 - Keep beta building with new cbindgen versions. a=lizzard\nTrivial change, just replacing Self by the actual type.", "files": ["gfx/wr/webrender_api/src/color.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c6246eb414a5e174d8afdbd3c269845ec83c7a67", "parents": ["9374f09f9b175e8cb258106e46d8392e3793949e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bogdan Tara \u003cbtara@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out 5 changesets (bug 1518863) For ES Lint failure a=backout\n\nBacked out changeset 11506a4e0fd8 (bug 1518863)\nBacked out changeset d94de0e08f52 (bug 1518863)\nBacked out changeset 4d96aa8bbf57 (bug 1518863)\nBacked out changeset b7e78201e26c (bug 1518863)\nBacked out changeset 037957225790 (bug 1518863)", "files": ["dom/chrome-webidl/WebExtensionPolicy.webidl", "dom/promise/Promise.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp", "toolkit/components/extensions/Extension.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionProcessScript.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/WebExtensionPolicy.cpp", "toolkit/components/extensions/WebExtensionPolicy.h", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_startup_request_handler.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-common.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e1652912e1d567f8ea49246ed6ee550920afe616", "parents": ["c6246eb414a5e174d8afdbd3c269845ec83c7a67"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552096024, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "btara@mozilla.com"}, "10858": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 0 - Minor extension protocol handler cleanup. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nThese are trivial issues that I'd rather keep out of the main patch.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21444", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "392c75fdaebbd9738e2fef7160169ae1e6df390c", "parents": ["e1652912e1d567f8ea49246ed6ee550920afe616"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 1 - Add ready promise to WebExtensionPolicy. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nThis adds a promise member to the stub WebExtensionPolicy objects that we\ncreate early during extension initialization which resolves when the real\nextension instance is ready to load content. This promise will be used by the\nextension protocol handler to delay loads until the framework is ready to\nhandle them.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21445", "files": ["dom/chrome-webidl/WebExtensionPolicy.webidl", "toolkit/components/extensions/Extension.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/WebExtensionPolicy.cpp", "toolkit/components/extensions/WebExtensionPolicy.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "29e17fe8593d1c8953e82e243767f0c0d9addad5", "parents": ["392c75fdaebbd9738e2fef7160169ae1e6df390c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 2 - Delay extension protocol requests until extension is ready. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nWe don't want extension protocol load requests to begin loading until the\nextension is far enough initialized to run code. If we load it before then,\nthe extension framework will either fail to recognize the extension entirely,\nor may begin running its scripts in an incomplete environment.\n\nThis patch adds a slow path which adds a promise handler and creats a stub\nchannel only in the case when the extension is not ready. In the normal,\nalready-initialized case, we take the more direct path.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21447", "files": ["dom/promise/Promise.cpp", "netwerk/protocol/res/ExtensionProtocolHandler.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f754bdfd46155e680afee58b230a1e08cf2c3b14", "parents": ["29e17fe8593d1c8953e82e243767f0c0d9addad5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 3 - Initialize stub extension policies in child during startup. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nWe already create early stub policy objects in the parent process during\nextension startup, so that early load attempts and policy queries can succeed\nduring startup and extension installation. This patch does the same for child\nprocesses, which likewise may be asked to load extension URLs early during\nstartup when they override the homepage or have pages loaded from session\nrestore.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21448", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/Extension.jsm", "toolkit/components/extensions/ExtensionProcessScript.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "24f6b74fe41c781c47c81eb69e737f60e0d0ca8f", "parents": ["f754bdfd46155e680afee58b230a1e08cf2c3b14"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1518863: Part 4 - Add tests. r=aswan, a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21449", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_startup_request_handler.js", "toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-common.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6719bb90ce8ae048c9366e92cff22dcedd59eae7", "parents": ["24f6b74fe41c781c47c81eb69e737f60e0d0ca8f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552097428, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null], "user": "maglione.k@gmail.com"}, "10859": {"changesets": [{"author": "Logan Smyth \u003cloganfsmyth@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530423 - Ensure breakpoints are added to newly-cloned JSScripts for existing sources. r=loganfsmyth a=lizzard\n\nSimilar to bug 1528654, we currently bail out too early and don't process all of the correct scripts when adding breakpoints.\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22355", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/thread.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/head_dbg.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/source-03.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_source-03.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/test_source-04.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/testactors.js", "devtools/server/tests/unit/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb07e38d917f7d605c23dec973b5811b9b9bd9a9", "parents": ["6719bb90ce8ae048c9366e92cff22dcedd59eae7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Neil Deakin \u003cneil@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1530594 - treat menulists as always being leaf frames. r=tnikkel a=lizzard\n\nSummary: ...false from IsLeafDynamic anyway, the only effect is that this one menulist is now not a leaf, allowing its content to be generated upfront. This particular menulist only has two items in it anyway so there shouldn't be a performance issue, r?tnikkel\n\nReviewers: tnikkel\n\nReviewed By: tnikkel\n\nBug #: 1530594\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22517", "files": ["layout/xul/nsMenuPopupFrame.cpp", "toolkit/content/tests/chrome/test_menulist_keynav.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0bc584b08a5f13eef5686c63cca8bfd3698b8c6e", "parents": ["fb07e38d917f7d605c23dec973b5811b9b9bd9a9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bogdan Tara \u003cbtara@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1522092 - Disable PanelMultiView's keyboard navigation code for the Site Identity panel. r=johannh a=lizzard\n\nSummary:\nPanelMultiView's keyboard navigation code currently overrides the arrow keys in menulists.\nThis breaks the permission selectors in the Site Identity panel.\nFor now, just disable this keyboard navigation code.\nDOM will then handle tabbing as it normally would.\nThis panel is more like a dialog than a menu, so users will generally navigate it with the tab key rather than the arrow keys anyway.\nNote that the code in PanelMultiView which makes controls focusable still runs even with disablekeynav set, which is what we want.\n\nReviewers: johannh\n\nReviewed By: johannh\n\nBug #: 1522092\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D21484", "files": ["browser/components/controlcenter/content/panel.inc.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c4d0a83454a291d01e5c8d2f9215a2d43c890562", "parents": ["0bc584b08a5f13eef5686c63cca8bfd3698b8c6e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Bogdan Tara \u003cbtara@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1528097 - U2F doesn't work on Windows 10 19H1/20H1 Insider builds r=jcj, keeler a=lizzard\n\nReviewers: jcj, keeler\n\nReviewed By: jcj, keeler\n\nSubscribers: reviewbot, jcj\n\nBug #: 1528097\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22343", "files": ["dom/u2f/U2F.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "93d78ef4e591cb9b980605691051abadaca9d773", "parents": ["c4d0a83454a291d01e5c8d2f9215a2d43c890562"], "tags": []}], "date": 1552105129, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "btara@mozilla.com"}, "10860": {"changesets": [{"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1532719 - Reset _pinnedUnscrollable flag when unpinning a tab. r=Gijs a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22474", "files": ["browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0b7f3caba2aa08835a4f252c6805c0224f029d98", "parents": ["93d78ef4e591cb9b980605691051abadaca9d773"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1527572 - Properly style the download panel summary. r=Felipe a=lizzard\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D22096", "files": ["browser/components/downloads/content/downloadsPanel.inc.xul", "browser/themes/shared/downloads/downloads.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4ed0c8d33336c4c811f85396b4233c54d782d766", "parents": ["0b7f3caba2aa08835a4f252c6805c0224f029d98"], "tags": ["FIREFOX_RELEASE_66_BASE"]}], "date": 1552183390, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "apavel@mozilla.com"}, "10861": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging mozilla-beta 4ed0c8d33336c4c811f85396b4233c54d782d766 with FIREFOX_RELEASE_66_BASE a=release DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9c40d87d4fe54be1394461636de5484bc5a9c51b", "parents": ["4ed0c8d33336c4c811f85396b4233c54d782d766"], "tags": ["FIREFOX_BETA_66_END"]}], "date": 1552305627, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld-merge"}}
